P_HTM[5]="*1. Aniccavaggo**Impermanence*";
P_HTM[6]="*1. Ajjhattāniccasuttaṃ**The Interior as Impermanent*";
P_HTM[7]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ.**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[8]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[9]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants,*";
P_HTM[10]="*“bhikkhavo”ti.**“Mendicants!”*";
P_HTM[11]="*“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ.**“Venerable sir,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[12]="*Bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said this:*";
P_HTM[13]="*“Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ.**“Mendicants, the eye is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[14]="*Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ;**What’s impermanent is suffering.*";
P_HTM[15]="*yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadanattā.**What’s suffering is not-self.*";
P_HTM[16]="*Yadanattā taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**And what’s not-self should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[17]="*Sotaṃ aniccaṃ.**The ear is impermanent. …*";
P_HTM[18]="*Yadaniccaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[19]="*ghānaṃ aniccaṃ.**The nose is impermanent. …*";
P_HTM[20]="*Yadaniccaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[21]="*jivhā aniccā.**The tongue is impermanent. …*";
P_HTM[22]="*Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[23]="*yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadanattā.* **";
P_HTM[24]="*Yadanattā taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[25]="*Kāyo anicco.**The body is impermanent. …*";
P_HTM[26]="*Yadaniccaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[27]="*mano anicco.**The mind is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[28]="*Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ;**What’s impermanent is suffering.*";
P_HTM[29]="*yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadanattā.**What’s suffering is not-self.*";
P_HTM[30]="*Yadanattā taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ.**And what’s not-self should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’*";
P_HTM[31]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, sotasmimpi nibbindati, ghānasmimpi nibbindati, jivhāyapi nibbindati, kāyasmimpi nibbindati, manasmimpi nibbindati.**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind.*";
P_HTM[32]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[33]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[34]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
