P_HTM[201]="*Dvādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[202]="*Aniccavaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[203]="*Aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ anattā ca,* **";
P_HTM[204]="*tayo ajjhattabāhirā;* **";
P_HTM[205]="*Yadaniccena tayo vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[206]="*te te ajjhattabāhirāti.* **";
P_HTM[207]="*2. Yamakavaggo**Pairs*";
P_HTM[208]="*1. Paṭhamapubbesambodhasuttaṃ**Before My Awakening (Interior)*";
P_HTM[209]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[210]="*“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi:**“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought:*";
P_HTM[211]="*‘ko nu kho cakkhussa assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ?**‘What’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to the eye …*";
P_HTM[212]="*Ko sotassa … pe …**ear …*";
P_HTM[213]="*ko ghānassa …**nose …*";
P_HTM[214]="*ko jivhāya …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[215]="*ko kāyassa …**body …*";
P_HTM[216]="*ko manassa assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan’ti?**and mind?’*";
P_HTM[217]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[218]="*‘yaṃ kho cakkhuṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ cakkhussa assādo.**‘The pleasure and happiness that arise from the eye: this is its gratification.*";
P_HTM[219]="*Yaṃ cakkhuṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, ayaṃ cakkhussa ādīnavo.**That the eye is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback.*";
P_HTM[220]="*Yo cakkhusmiṃ chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ cakkhussa nissaraṇaṃ.**Removing and giving up desire and greed for the eye: this is its escape.*";
P_HTM[221]="*Yaṃ sotaṃ … pe …**The pleasure and happiness that arise from the ear …*";
P_HTM[222]="*yaṃ ghānaṃ … pe …**nose …*";
P_HTM[223]="*yaṃ jivhaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ jivhāya assādo.**tongue …*";
P_HTM[224]="*Yaṃ jivhā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ jivhāya ādīnavo.* **";
P_HTM[225]="*Yo jivhāya chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ jivhāya nissaraṇaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[226]="*Yaṃ kāyaṃ … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[227]="*yaṃ manaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ manassa assādo.**mind: this is its gratification.*";
P_HTM[228]="*Yaṃ mano anicco dukkho vipariṇāmadhammo, ayaṃ manassa ādīnavo.**That the mind is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback.*";
P_HTM[229]="*Yo manasmiṃ chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ manassa nissaraṇan’ti.**Removing and giving up desire and greed for the mind: this is its escape.’*";
P_HTM[230]="*Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ channaṃ ajjhattikānaṃ āyatanānaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññāsiṃ, neva tāvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya ‘anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ.**As long as I didn’t truly understand these six interior sense fields’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are, I didn’t announce my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[231]="*Yato ca khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ channaṃ ajjhattikānaṃ āyatanānaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, athāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya ‘anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ.**But when I did truly understand these six interior sense fields’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are, I announced my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.*";
P_HTM[232]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:**Knowledge and vision arose in me:*";
P_HTM[233]="*‘akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti.**‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more future lives.’”*";
P_HTM[234]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[235]="*2. Dutiyapubbesambodhasuttaṃ**Before My Awakening (Exterior)*";
P_HTM[236]="*“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi:**“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought:*";
P_HTM[237]="*‘ko nu kho rūpānaṃ assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ?**‘What’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to sights …*";
P_HTM[238]="*Ko saddānaṃ … pe …**sounds …*";
P_HTM[239]="*ko gandhānaṃ …**smells …*";
P_HTM[240]="*ko rasānaṃ …**tastes …*";
P_HTM[241]="*ko phoṭṭhabbānaṃ …**touches …*";
P_HTM[242]="*ko dhammānaṃ assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan’ti?**and thoughts?’ …”*";
P_HTM[243]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[244]="*‘yaṃ kho rūpe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ rūpānaṃ assādo.* **";
P_HTM[245]="*Yaṃ rūpā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ rūpānaṃ ādīnavo.* **";
P_HTM[246]="*Yo rūpesu chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[247]="*Yaṃ sadde …* **";
P_HTM[248]="*gandhe …* **";
P_HTM[249]="*rase …* **";
P_HTM[250]="*phoṭṭhabbe …* **";
P_HTM[251]="*yaṃ dhamme paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ dhammānaṃ assādo.* **";
P_HTM[252]="*Yaṃ dhammā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ dhammānaṃ ādīnavo.* **";
P_HTM[253]="*Yo dhammesu chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ dhammānaṃ nissaraṇan’ti.* **";
P_HTM[254]="*Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ channaṃ bāhirānaṃ āyatanānaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññāsiṃ, neva tāvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya ‘anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[255]="*Yato ca khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ channaṃ bāhirānaṃ āyatanānaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, athāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya ‘anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[256]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:* **";
P_HTM[257]="*‘akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[258]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[259]="*3. Paṭhamaassādapariyesanasuttaṃ**In Search of Gratification (Interior)*";
P_HTM[260]="*“Cakkhussāhaṃ, bhikkhave, assādapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.**“Mendicants, I went in search of the eye’s gratification,*";
P_HTM[261]="*Yo cakkhussa assādo tadajjhagamaṃ.**and I found it.*";
P_HTM[262]="*Yāvatā cakkhussa assādo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.**I’ve seen clearly with wisdom the full extent of the eye’s gratification.*";
P_HTM[263]="*Cakkhussāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ādīnavapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.**I went in search of the eye’s drawback,*";
P_HTM[264]="*Yo cakkhussa ādīnavo tadajjhagamaṃ.**and I found it.*";
P_HTM[265]="*Yāvatā cakkhussa ādīnavo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.**I’ve seen clearly with wisdom the full extent of the eye’s drawback.*";
P_HTM[266]="*Cakkhussāhaṃ, bhikkhave, nissaraṇapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.**I went in search of escape from the eye,*";
P_HTM[267]="*Yaṃ cakkhussa nissaraṇaṃ tadajjhagamaṃ.**and I found it.*";
P_HTM[268]="*Yāvatā cakkhussa nissaraṇaṃ, paññāya me taṃ sudiṭṭhaṃ.**I’ve seen clearly with wisdom the full extent of escape from the eye.*";
P_HTM[269]="*Sotassāhaṃ, bhikkhave …**I went in search of the ear’s …*";
P_HTM[270]="*ghānassāhaṃ, bhikkhave …**nose’s …*";
P_HTM[271]="*jivhāyāhaṃ bhikkhave, assādapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.**tongue’s …*";
P_HTM[272]="*Yo jivhāya assādo tadajjhagamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[273]="*Yāvatā jivhāya assādo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.* **";
P_HTM[274]="*Jivhāyāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ādīnavapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.* **";
P_HTM[275]="*Yo jivhāya ādīnavo tadajjhagamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[276]="*Yāvatā jivhāya ādīnavo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.* **";
P_HTM[277]="*Jivhāyāhaṃ, bhikkhave, nissaraṇapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.* **";
P_HTM[278]="*Yaṃ jivhāya nissaraṇaṃ tadajjhagamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[279]="*Yāvatā jivhāya nissaraṇaṃ, paññāya me taṃ sudiṭṭhaṃ … pe …**body’s …*";
P_HTM[280]="*manassāhaṃ, bhikkhave, assādapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.**mind’s gratification,*";
P_HTM[281]="*Yo manassa assādo tadajjhagamaṃ.**and I found it.*";
P_HTM[282]="*Yāvatā manassa assādo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.**I’ve seen clearly with wisdom the full extent of the mind’s gratification.*";
P_HTM[283]="*Manassāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ādīnavapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.**I went in search of the mind’s drawback,*";
P_HTM[284]="*Yo manassa ādīnavo tadajjhagamaṃ.**and I found it.*";
P_HTM[285]="*Yāvatā manassa ādīnavo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.**I’ve seen clearly with wisdom the full extent of the mind’s drawback.*";
P_HTM[286]="*Manassāhaṃ, bhikkhave, nissaraṇapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.**I went in search of escape from the mind,*";
P_HTM[287]="*Yaṃ manassa nissaraṇaṃ tadajjhagamaṃ.**and I found it.*";
P_HTM[288]="*Yāvatā manassa nissaraṇaṃ, paññāya me taṃ sudiṭṭhaṃ.**I’ve seen clearly with wisdom the full extent of escape from the mind.*";
P_HTM[289]="*Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ channaṃ ajjhattikānaṃ āyatanānaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññāsiṃ … pe …**As long as I didn’t truly understand these six interior sense fields’ gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are, I didn’t announce my supreme perfect awakening …*";
P_HTM[290]="*paccaññāsiṃ.**But when I did truly understand …*";
P_HTM[291]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:**Knowledge and vision arose in me:*";
P_HTM[292]="*‘akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti.**‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more future lives.’”*";
P_HTM[293]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[294]="*4. Dutiyaassādapariyesanasuttaṃ**In Search of Gratification (Exterior)*";
P_HTM[295]="*“Rūpānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, assādapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.**“Mendicants, I went in search of the gratification of sights,*";
P_HTM[296]="*Yo rūpānaṃ assādo tadajjhagamaṃ.**and I found it. …”*";
P_HTM[297]="*Yāvatā rūpānaṃ assādo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.* **";
P_HTM[298]="*Rūpānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ādīnavapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.* **";
P_HTM[299]="*Yo rūpānaṃ ādīnavo tadajjhagamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[300]="*Yāvatā rūpānaṃ ādīnavo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.* **";
P_HTM[301]="*Rūpānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, nissaraṇapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.* **";
P_HTM[302]="*Yaṃ rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ tadajjhagamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[303]="*Yāvatā rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ, paññāya me taṃ sudiṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[304]="*Saddānāhaṃ, bhikkhave …* **";
P_HTM[305]="*gandhānāhaṃ, bhikkhave …* **";
P_HTM[306]="*rasānāhaṃ, bhikkhave …* **";
P_HTM[307]="*phoṭṭhabbānāhaṃ, bhikkhave …* **";
P_HTM[308]="*dhammānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, assādapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.* **";
P_HTM[309]="*Yo dhammānaṃ assādo tadajjhagamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[310]="*Yāvatā dhammānaṃ assādo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.* **";
P_HTM[311]="*Dhammānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ādīnavapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.* **";
P_HTM[312]="*Yo dhammānaṃ ādīnavo tadajjhagamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[313]="*Yāvatā dhammānaṃ ādīnavo paññāya me so sudiṭṭho.* **";
P_HTM[314]="*Dhammānāhaṃ, bhikkhave, nissaraṇapariyesanaṃ acariṃ.* **";
P_HTM[315]="*Yaṃ dhammānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ tadajjhagamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[316]="*Yāvatā dhammānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ, paññāya me taṃ sudiṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[317]="*Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ channaṃ bāhirānaṃ āyatanānaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññāsiṃ … pe … paccaññāsiṃ.* **";
P_HTM[318]="*Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi:* **";
P_HTM[319]="*‘akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[320]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[321]="*5. Paṭhamanoceassādasuttaṃ**If There Were No Gratification (Interior)*";
P_HTM[322]="*“No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, cakkhussa assādo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā cakkhusmiṃ sārajjeyyuṃ.**“Mendicants, if there were no gratification in the eye, sentient beings wouldn’t love it.*";
P_HTM[323]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi cakkhussa assādo tasmā sattā cakkhusmiṃ sārajjanti.**But because there is gratification in the eye, sentient beings do love it.*";
P_HTM[324]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, cakkhussa ādīnavo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā cakkhusmiṃ nibbindeyyuṃ.**If the eye had no drawback, sentient beings wouldn’t grow disillusioned with it.*";
P_HTM[325]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi cakkhussa ādīnavo tasmā sattā cakkhusmiṃ nibbindanti.**But because the eye has a drawback, sentient beings do grow disillusioned with it.*";
P_HTM[326]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, cakkhussa nissaraṇaṃ abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā cakkhusmā nissareyyuṃ.**If there were no escape from the eye, sentient beings wouldn’t escape from it.*";
P_HTM[327]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi cakkhussa nissaraṇaṃ tasmā sattā cakkhusmā nissaranti.**But because there is an escape from the eye, sentient beings do escape from it.*";
P_HTM[328]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, sotassa assādo abhavissa …**If there were no gratification in the ear …*";
P_HTM[329]="*no cedaṃ, bhikkhave, ghānassa assādo abhavissa …**nose …*";
P_HTM[330]="*no cedaṃ, bhikkhave, jivhāya assādo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā jivhāya sārajjeyyuṃ.**tongue …*";
P_HTM[331]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi jivhāya assādo, tasmā sattā jivhāya sārajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[332]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, jivhāya ādīnavo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā jivhāya nibbindeyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[333]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi jivhāya ādīnavo, tasmā sattā jivhāya nibbindanti.* **";
P_HTM[334]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, jivhāya nissaraṇaṃ abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā jivhāya nissareyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[335]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi jivhāya nissaraṇaṃ, tasmā sattā jivhāya nissaranti.* **";
P_HTM[336]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, kāyassa assādo abhavissa …**body …*";
P_HTM[337]="*no cedaṃ, bhikkhave, manassa assādo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā manasmiṃ sārajjeyyuṃ.**mind, sentient beings wouldn’t love it.*";
P_HTM[338]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi manassa assādo, tasmā sattā manasmiṃ sārajjanti.**But because there is gratification in the mind, sentient beings do love it.*";
P_HTM[339]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, manassa ādīnavo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā manasmiṃ nibbindeyyuṃ.**If the mind had no drawback, sentient beings wouldn’t grow disillusioned with it.*";
P_HTM[340]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi manassa ādīnavo, tasmā sattā manasmiṃ nibbindanti.**But because the mind has a drawback, sentient beings do grow disillusioned with it.*";
P_HTM[341]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, manassa nissaraṇaṃ abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā manasmā nissareyyuṃ.**If there were no escape from the mind, sentient beings wouldn’t escape from it.*";
P_HTM[342]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi manassa nissaraṇaṃ, tasmā sattā manasmā nissaranti.**But because there is an escape from the mind, sentient beings do escape from it.*";
P_HTM[343]="*Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, sattā imesaṃ channaṃ ajjhattikānaṃ āyatanānaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññaṃsu, neva tāva, bhikkhave, sattā sadevakā lokā samārakā sabrahmakā sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya nissaṭā visaññuttā vippamuttā vimariyādīkatena cetasā vihariṃsu.**As long as sentient beings don’t truly understand these six interior sense fields’ gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are, they haven’t escaped from this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—and they don’t live detached, liberated, with a mind free of limits.*";
P_HTM[344]="*Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, sattā imesaṃ channaṃ ajjhattikānaṃ āyatanānaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññaṃsu, atha, bhikkhave, sattā sadevakā lokā samārakā sabrahmakā sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya nissaṭā visaññuttā vippamuttā vimariyādīkatena cetasā viharantī”ti.**But when sentient beings truly understand these six interior sense fields’ gratification, drawback, and escape for what they are, they’ve escaped from this world—with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—and they live detached, liberated, with a mind free of limits.”*";
P_HTM[345]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[346]="*6. Dutiyanoceassādasuttaṃ**If There Were No Gratification (Exterior)*";
P_HTM[347]="*“No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ assādo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā rūpesu sārajjeyyuṃ.**“Mendicants, if there were no gratification in sights, sentient beings wouldn’t love them. …”*";
P_HTM[348]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi rūpānaṃ assādo, tasmā sattā rūpesu sārajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[349]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ ādīnavo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā rūpesu nibbindeyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[350]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi rūpānaṃ ādīnavo, tasmā sattā rūpesu nibbindanti.* **";
P_HTM[351]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā rūpehi nissareyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[352]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi rūpānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ, tasmā sattā rūpehi nissaranti.* **";
P_HTM[353]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, saddānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[354]="*gandhānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[355]="*rasānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[356]="*phoṭṭhabbānaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[357]="*dhammānaṃ assādo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā dhammesu sārajjeyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[358]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi dhammānaṃ assādo, tasmā sattā dhammesu sārajjanti.* **";
P_HTM[359]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ ādīnavo abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā dhammesu nibbindeyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[360]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi dhammānaṃ ādīnavo, tasmā sattā dhammesu nibbindanti.* **";
P_HTM[361]="*No cedaṃ, bhikkhave, dhammānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ abhavissa, nayidaṃ sattā dhammehi nissareyyuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[362]="*Yasmā ca kho, bhikkhave, atthi dhammānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ, tasmā sattā dhammehi nissaranti.* **";
P_HTM[363]="*Yāvakīvañca, bhikkhave, sattā imesaṃ channaṃ bāhirānaṃ āyatanānaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññaṃsu, neva tāva, bhikkhave, sattā sadevakā lokā samārakā sabrahmakā sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya nissaṭā visaññuttā vippamuttā vimariyādīkatena cetasā vihariṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[364]="*Yato ca kho, bhikkhave, sattā imesaṃ channaṃ bāhirānaṃ āyatanānaṃ assādañca assādato, ādīnavañca ādīnavato, nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññaṃsu, atha, bhikkhave, sattā sadevakā lokā samārakā sabrahmakā sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya nissaṭā visaññuttā vippamuttā vimariyādīkatena cetasā viharantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[365]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[366]="*7. Paṭhamābhinandasuttaṃ**Taking Pleasure (Interior)*";
P_HTM[367]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, cakkhuṃ abhinandati, dukkhaṃ so abhinandati.**“Mendicants, if you take pleasure in the eye, you take pleasure in suffering.*";
P_HTM[368]="*Yo dukkhaṃ abhinandati, aparimutto so dukkhasmāti vadāmi.**If you take pleasure in suffering, I say you’re not exempt from suffering.*";
P_HTM[369]="*Yo sotaṃ … pe …**If you take pleasure in the ear …*";
P_HTM[370]="*yo ghānaṃ … pe …**nose …*";
P_HTM[371]="*yo jivhaṃ abhinandati, dukkhaṃ so abhinandati.**tongue …*";
P_HTM[372]="*Yo dukkhaṃ abhinandati, aparimutto so dukkhasmā”ti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[373]="*Yo kāyaṃ … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[374]="*yo manaṃ abhinandati, dukkhaṃ so abhinandati.**mind, you take pleasure in suffering.*";
P_HTM[375]="*Yo dukkhaṃ abhinandati, aparimutto so dukkhasmā”ti vadāmi.**If you take pleasure in suffering, I say you’re not exempt from suffering.*";
P_HTM[376]="*“Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, cakkhuṃ nābhinandati, dukkhaṃ so nābhinandati.**If you don’t take pleasure in the eye, you don’t take pleasure in suffering.*";
P_HTM[377]="*Yo dukkhaṃ nābhinandati, parimutto so dukkhasmāti vadāmi.**If you don’t take pleasure in suffering, I say you’re exempt from suffering.*";
P_HTM[378]="*Yo sotaṃ … pe …**If you don’t take pleasure in the ear …*";
P_HTM[379]="*yo ghānaṃ … pe …**nose …*";
P_HTM[380]="*yo jivhaṃ nābhinandati, dukkhaṃ so nābhinandati.**tongue …*";
P_HTM[381]="*Yo dukkhaṃ nābhinandati, parimutto so dukkhasmāti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[382]="*Yo kāyaṃ … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[383]="*yo manaṃ nābhinandati, dukkhaṃ so nābhinandati.**mind, you don’t take pleasure in suffering.*";
P_HTM[384]="*Yo dukkhaṃ nābhinandati, parimutto so dukkhasmā”ti vadāmi.**If you don’t take pleasure in suffering, I say you’re exempt from suffering.”*";
P_HTM[385]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[386]="*8. Dutiyābhinandasuttaṃ**Taking Pleasure (Exterior)*";
P_HTM[387]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, rūpe abhinandati, dukkhaṃ so abhinandati.**“Mendicants, if you take pleasure in sights, you take pleasure in suffering.*";
P_HTM[388]="*Yo dukkhaṃ abhinandati, aparimutto so dukkhasmāti vadāmi.**If you take pleasure in suffering, I say you’re not exempt from suffering. …”*";
P_HTM[389]="*Yo sadde … pe …* **";
P_HTM[390]="*gandhe …* **";
P_HTM[391]="*rase …* **";
P_HTM[392]="*phoṭṭhabbe …* **";
P_HTM[393]="*dhamme abhinandati, dukkhaṃ so abhinandati.* **";
P_HTM[394]="*Yo dukkhaṃ abhinandati, aparimutto so dukkhasmā”ti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[395]="*“Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, rūpe nābhinandati, dukkhaṃ so nābhinandati.* **";
P_HTM[396]="*Yo dukkhaṃ nābhinandati, parimutto so dukkhasmā”ti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[397]="*Yo sadde … pe …* **";
P_HTM[398]="*gandhe …* **";
P_HTM[399]="*rase …* **";
P_HTM[400]="*phoṭṭhabbe …* **";
P_HTM[401]="*dhamme nābhinandati, dukkhaṃ so nābhinandati.* **";
P_HTM[402]="*Yo dukkhaṃ nābhinandati, parimutto so dukkhasmā”ti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[403]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[404]="*9. Paṭhamadukkhuppādasuttaṃ**The Arising of Suffering (Interior)*";
P_HTM[405]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, cakkhussa uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**“Mendicants, the arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of the eye is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[406]="*Yo sotassa … pe …**The arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of the ear …*";
P_HTM[407]="*yo ghānassa …**nose …*";
P_HTM[408]="*yo jivhāya …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[409]="*yo kāyassa …**body …*";
P_HTM[410]="*yo manassa uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**and mind is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[411]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, cakkhussa nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo.**The cessation, settling, and ending of the eye is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[412]="*Yo sotassa …**The cessation, settling, and ending of the ear,*";
P_HTM[413]="*yo ghānassa …**nose,*";
P_HTM[414]="*yo jivhāya …**tongue,*";
P_HTM[415]="*yo kāyassa …**body,*";
P_HTM[416]="*yo manassa nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**and mind is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[417]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[418]="*10. Dutiyadukkhuppādasuttaṃ**The Arising of Suffering (Exterior)*";
P_HTM[419]="*“Yo, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**“Mendicants, the arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of sights is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[420]="*Yo saddānaṃ … pe …**The arising, continuation, rebirth, and manifestation of sounds,*";
P_HTM[421]="*yo gandhānaṃ …**smells,*";
P_HTM[422]="*yo rasānaṃ …**tastes,*";
P_HTM[423]="*yo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ …**touches,*";
P_HTM[424]="*yo dhammānaṃ uppādo ṭhiti abhinibbatti pātubhāvo, dukkhasseso uppādo, rogānaṃ ṭhiti, jarāmaraṇassa pātubhāvo.**and thoughts is the arising of suffering, the continuation of diseases, and the manifestation of old age and death.*";
P_HTM[425]="*Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, rūpānaṃ nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo.**The cessation, settling, and ending of sights,*";
P_HTM[426]="*Yo saddānaṃ … pe …**sounds,*";
P_HTM[427]="*yo gandhānaṃ …**smells,*";
P_HTM[428]="*yo rasānaṃ …**tastes,*";
P_HTM[429]="*yo phoṭṭhabbānaṃ …**touches,*";
P_HTM[430]="*yo dhammānaṃ nirodho vūpasamo atthaṅgamo, dukkhasseso nirodho, rogānaṃ vūpasamo, jarāmaraṇassa atthaṅgamo”ti.**and thoughts is the cessation of suffering, the settling of diseases, and the ending of old age and death.”*";
P_HTM[431]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[432]="*Yamakavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[433]="*Sambodhena duve vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[434]="*Assādena apare duve;* **";
P_HTM[435]="*No cetena duve vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[436]="*Abhinandena apare duve;* **";
P_HTM[437]="*Uppādena duve vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[438]="*Vaggo tena pavuccatīti.* **";
P_HTM[439]="*3. Sabbavaggo**All*";
P_HTM[440]="*1. Sabbasuttaṃ**All*";
P_HTM[441]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[442]="*“Sabbaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the all.*";
P_HTM[443]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[444]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ?**And what is the all?*";
P_HTM[445]="*Cakkhuñceva rūpā ca, sotañca saddā ca, ghānañca gandhā ca, jivhā ca rasā ca, kāyo ca phoṭṭhabbā ca, mano ca dhammā ca—**It’s just the eye and sights, the ear and sounds, the nose and smells, the tongue and tastes, the body and touches, and the mind and thoughts.*";
P_HTM[446]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ.**This is called the all.*";
P_HTM[447]="*Yo, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya:**Mendicants, suppose someone was to say:*";
P_HTM[448]="*‘ahametaṃ sabbaṃ paccakkhāya aññaṃ sabbaṃ paññāpessāmī’ti, tassa vācāvatthukamevassa;**‘I’ll reject this all and describe another all.’ They’d have no grounds for that,*";
P_HTM[449]="*puṭṭho ca na sampāyeyya, uttariñca vighātaṃ āpajjeyya.**they’d be stumped by questions, and, in addition, they’d get frustrated.*";
P_HTM[450]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[451]="*Yathā taṃ, bhikkhave, avisayasmin”ti.**Because they’re out of their element.”*";
P_HTM[452]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[453]="*2. Pahānasuttaṃ**Giving Up*";
P_HTM[454]="*“Sabbappahānāya vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the principle for giving up the all.*";
P_HTM[455]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[456]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sabbappahānāya dhammo?**And what is the principle for giving up the all?*";
P_HTM[457]="*Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, pahātabbaṃ, rūpā pahātabbā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ pahātabbaṃ, cakkhusamphasso pahātabbo, yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi pahātabbaṃ … pe …**The eye should be given up. Sights should be given up. Eye consciousness should be given up. Eye contact should be given up. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact should also be given up.*";
P_HTM[458]="*jivhā pahātabbā, rasā pahātabbā, jivhāviññāṇaṃ pahātabbaṃ, jivhāsamphasso pahātabbo, yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi pahātabbaṃ.**tongue …*";
P_HTM[459]="*Kāyo pahātabbo …**body …*";
P_HTM[460]="*mano pahātabbo, dhammā pahātabbā, manoviññāṇaṃ pahātabbaṃ, manosamphasso pahātabbo, yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi pahātabbaṃ.**mind should be given up. Thoughts should be given up. Mind consciousness should be given up. Mind contact should be given up. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact should be given up.*";
P_HTM[461]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbappahānāya dhammo”ti.**This is the principle for giving up the all.”*";
P_HTM[462]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[463]="*3. Abhiññāpariññāpahānasuttaṃ**Giving Up By Direct Knowledge and Complete Understanding*";
P_HTM[464]="*“Sabbaṃ abhiññā pariññā pahānāya vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the principle for giving up the all by direct knowledge and complete understanding.*";
P_HTM[465]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[466]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ abhiññā pariññā pahānāya dhammo?**And what is the principle for giving up the all by direct knowledge and complete understanding?*";
P_HTM[467]="*Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, abhiññā pariññā pahātabbaṃ, rūpā abhiññā pariññā pahātabbā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ abhiññā pariññā pahātabbaṃ, cakkhusamphasso abhiññā pariññā pahātabbo, yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi abhiññā pariññā pahātabbaṃ … pe …**The eye should be given up by direct knowledge and complete understanding. Sights should be given up by direct knowledge and complete understanding. Eye consciousness should be given up by direct knowledge and complete understanding. Eye contact should be given up by direct knowledge and complete understanding. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact should be given up by direct knowledge and complete understanding.*";
P_HTM[468]="*jivhā abhiññā pariññā pahātabbā, rasā abhiññā pariññā pahātabbā, jivhāviññāṇaṃ abhiññā pariññā pahātabbaṃ, jivhāsamphasso abhiññā pariññā pahātabbo, yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi abhiññā pariññā pahātabbaṃ.**tongue …*";
P_HTM[469]="*Kāyo abhiññā pariññā pahātabbo …**body …*";
P_HTM[470]="*mano abhiññā pariññā pahātabbo, dhammā abhiññā pariññā pahātabbā, manoviññāṇaṃ abhiññā pariññā pahātabbaṃ, manosamphasso abhiññā pariññā pahātabbo, yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi abhiññā pariññā pahātabbaṃ.**mind should be given up by direct knowledge and complete understanding. Thoughts should be given up by direct knowledge and complete understanding. Mind consciousness should be given up by direct knowledge and complete understanding. Mind contact should be given up by direct knowledge and complete understanding. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact should be given up by direct knowledge and complete understanding.*";
P_HTM[471]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ abhiññā pariññā pahānāya dhammo”ti.**This is the principle for giving up the all by direct knowledge and complete understanding.”*";
P_HTM[472]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[473]="*4. Paṭhamaaparijānanasuttaṃ**Without Completely Understanding (1st)*";
P_HTM[474]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**“Mendicants, without directly knowing and completely understanding the all, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[475]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya?**And what is the all, without directly knowing and completely understanding which, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering?*";
P_HTM[476]="*Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**Without directly knowing and completely understanding the eye, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[477]="*Rūpe anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**Without directly knowing and completely understanding sights …*";
P_HTM[478]="*Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**eye consciousness …*";
P_HTM[479]="*Cakkhusamphassaṃ anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**eye contact …*";
P_HTM[480]="*Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya … pe …**painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[481]="*jivhaṃ anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**Without directly knowing and completely understanding the ear … the nose … the tongue …*";
P_HTM[482]="*Rase … pe …* **";
P_HTM[483]="*jivhāviññāṇaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[484]="*jivhāsamphassaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[485]="*yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.* **";
P_HTM[486]="*Kāyaṃ … pe …**the body …*";
P_HTM[487]="*manaṃ anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**the mind, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[488]="*Dhamme … pe …**Without directly knowing and completely understanding thoughts …*";
P_HTM[489]="*manoviññāṇaṃ … pe …**mind consciousness …*";
P_HTM[490]="*manosamphassaṃ … pe …**mind contact …*";
P_HTM[491]="*yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[492]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**This is the all, without directly knowing and completely understanding which, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[493]="*Sabbañca kho, bhikkhave, abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**By directly knowing and completely understanding the all, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering.*";
P_HTM[494]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya?**And what is the all, directly knowing and completely understanding which, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering?*";
P_HTM[495]="*Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**By directly knowing and completely understanding the eye …*";
P_HTM[496]="*Rūpe abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.* **";
P_HTM[497]="*Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.* **";
P_HTM[498]="*Cakkhusamphassaṃ abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.* **";
P_HTM[499]="*Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya … pe …* **";
P_HTM[500]="*jivhaṃ abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**the ear … the nose … the tongue …*";
P_HTM[501]="*Rase … pe …* **";
P_HTM[502]="*jivhāviññāṇaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[503]="*jivhāsamphassaṃ … pe …* **";
P_HTM[504]="*yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.* **";
P_HTM[505]="*Kāyaṃ … pe …**the body …*";
P_HTM[506]="*manaṃ abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**the mind, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering.*";
P_HTM[507]="*Dhamme … pe …**By directly knowing and completely understanding thoughts …*";
P_HTM[508]="*manoviññāṇaṃ … pe …**mind consciousness …*";
P_HTM[509]="*manosamphassaṃ … pe …**mind contact …*";
P_HTM[510]="*yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering.*";
P_HTM[511]="*Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāyā”ti.**This is the all, directly knowing and completely understanding which, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering.”*";
P_HTM[512]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[513]="*5. Dutiyaaparijānanasuttaṃ**Without Completely Understanding (2nd)*";
P_HTM[514]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**“Mendicants, without directly knowing and completely understanding the all, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[515]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya?**And what is the all, without directly knowing and completely understanding which, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering?*";
P_HTM[516]="*Yañca, bhikkhave, cakkhu, ye ca rūpā, yañca cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, ye ca cakkhuviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā … pe …**The eye, sights, eye consciousness, and things known by eye consciousness.*";
P_HTM[517]="*yā ca jivhā, ye ca rasā, yañca jivhāviññāṇaṃ, ye ca jivhāviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā;**The ear … nose … tongue …*";
P_HTM[518]="*yo ca kāyo, ye ca phoṭṭhabbā, yañca kāyaviññāṇaṃ, ye ca kāyaviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā;**body …*";
P_HTM[519]="*yo ca mano, ye ca dhammā, yañca manoviññāṇaṃ, ye ca manoviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā—**The mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and things known by mind consciousness.*";
P_HTM[520]="*idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**This is the all, without directly knowing and completely understanding which, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[521]="*Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**By directly knowing and completely understanding the all, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering.*";
P_HTM[522]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya?**And what is the all, directly knowing and completely understanding which, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering?*";
P_HTM[523]="*Yañca, bhikkhave, cakkhu, ye ca rūpā, yañca cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, ye ca cakkhuviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā … pe …**The eye, sights, eye consciousness, and things known by eye consciousness.*";
P_HTM[524]="*yā ca jivhā, ye ca rasā, yañca jivhāviññāṇaṃ, ye ca jivhāviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā;**The ear … nose … tongue …*";
P_HTM[525]="*yo ca kāyo, ye ca phoṭṭhabbā, yañca kāyaviññāṇaṃ, ye ca kāyaviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā;**body …*";
P_HTM[526]="*yo ca mano, ye ca dhammā, yañca manoviññāṇaṃ, ye ca manoviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā—**The mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and things known by mind consciousness.*";
P_HTM[527]="*idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāyā”ti.**This is the all, directly knowing and completely understanding which, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering.”*";
P_HTM[528]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[529]="*6. Ādittasuttaṃ**Burning*";
P_HTM[530]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā gayāyaṃ viharati gayāsīse saddhiṃ bhikkhusahassena.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Gayā on Gayā Head together with a thousand mendicants.*";
P_HTM[531]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[532]="*“sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, ādittaṃ.**“Mendicants, all is burning.*";
P_HTM[533]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ ādittaṃ?**And what is the all that is burning?*";
P_HTM[534]="*Cakkhu, bhikkhave, ādittaṃ, rūpā ādittā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ ādittaṃ, cakkhusamphasso āditto. Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi ādittaṃ.**The eye is burning. Sights are burning. Eye consciousness is burning. Eye contact is burning. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact is also burning.*";
P_HTM[535]="*Kena ādittaṃ?**Burning with what?*";
P_HTM[536]="*‘Rāgagginā, dosagginā, mohagginā ādittaṃ, jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi ādittan’ti vadāmi … pe …**Burning with the fires of greed, hate, and delusion. Burning with rebirth, old age, and death, with sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[537]="*jivhā ādittā, rasā ādittā, jivhāviññāṇaṃ ādittaṃ, jivhāsamphasso āditto. Yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi ādittaṃ.**The ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[538]="*Kena ādittaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[539]="*‘Rāgagginā, dosagginā, mohagginā ādittaṃ, jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi ādittan’ti vadāmi … pe …* **";
P_HTM[540]="*mano āditto, dhammā ādittā, manoviññāṇaṃ ādittaṃ, manosamphasso āditto. Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi ādittaṃ.**The mind is burning. Thoughts are burning. Mind consciousness is burning. Mind contact is burning. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact is also burning.*";
P_HTM[541]="*Kena ādittaṃ?**Burning with what?*";
P_HTM[542]="*‘Rāgagginā, dosagginā, mohagginā ādittaṃ, jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi ādittan’ti vadāmi.**Burning with the fires of greed, hate, and delusion. Burning with rebirth, old age, and death, with sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, I say.*";
P_HTM[543]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati, yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati … pe …**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact.*";
P_HTM[544]="*yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati.**They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body … mind … painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact.*";
P_HTM[545]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[546]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[547]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[548]="*Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanduṃ.**Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[549]="*Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne tassa bhikkhusahassassa anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsūti.**And while this discourse was being spoken, the minds of the thousand mendicants were freed from defilements by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[550]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[551]="*7. Addhabhūtasuttaṃ**Oppressed*";
P_HTM[552]="*Evaṃ me sutaṃ—**So I have heard.*";
P_HTM[553]="*ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[554]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[555]="*“sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, addhabhūtaṃ.**“Mendicants, all is oppressed.*";
P_HTM[556]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ addhabhūtaṃ?**And what is the all that is oppressed?*";
P_HTM[557]="*Cakkhu, bhikkhave, addhabhūtaṃ, rūpā addhabhūtā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ addhabhūtaṃ, cakkhusamphasso addhabhūto, yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi addhabhūtaṃ.**The eye is oppressed. Sights are oppressed. Eye consciousness is oppressed. Eye contact is oppressed. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact is also oppressed.*";
P_HTM[558]="*Kena addhabhūtaṃ?**Oppressed by what?*";
P_HTM[559]="*‘Jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi addhabhūtan’ti vadāmi … pe …**Oppressed by the fires of greed, hate, and delusion. Oppressed by rebirth, old age, and death, by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, I say.*";
P_HTM[560]="*jivhā addhabhūtā, rasā addhabhūtā, jivhāviññāṇaṃ addhabhūtaṃ, jivhāsamphasso addhabhūto, yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi addhabhūtaṃ.**The ear … nose … tongue …*";
P_HTM[561]="*Kena addhabhūtaṃ?* **";
P_HTM[562]="*‘Jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi addhabhūtan’ti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[563]="*Kāyo addhabhūto … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[564]="*mano addhabhūto, dhammā addhabhūtā, manoviññāṇaṃ addhabhūtaṃ, manosamphasso addhabhūto, yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi addhabhūtaṃ.**mind is oppressed. Thoughts are oppressed. Mind consciousness is oppressed. Mind contact is oppressed. The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact is also oppressed.*";
P_HTM[565]="*Kena addhabhūtaṃ?**Oppressed by what?*";
P_HTM[566]="*‘Jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi addhabhūtan’ti vadāmi.**Oppressed by greed, hate, and delusion. Oppressed by rebirth, old age, and death, by sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, I say.*";
P_HTM[567]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati … pe …**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact.*";
P_HTM[568]="*yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati.**They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body … mind … painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact.*";
P_HTM[569]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati, virāgā vimuccati, vimuttasmiṃ ‘vimuttam’iti ñāṇaṃ hoti,**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[570]="*‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[571]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[572]="*8. Samugghātasāruppasuttaṃ**The Practice Fit for Uprooting*";
P_HTM[573]="*“Sabbamaññitasamugghātasāruppaṃ vo, bhikkhave, paṭipadaṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the practice fit for uprooting all identifying.*";
P_HTM[574]="*Taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmīti.**Listen and pay close attention, I will speak. …*";
P_HTM[575]="*Katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, sabbamaññitasamugghātasāruppā paṭipadā?**And what is the practice fit for uprooting all identifying?*";
P_HTM[576]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhuṃ na maññati, cakkhusmiṃ na maññati, cakkhuto na maññati, cakkhuṃ meti na maññati.**It’s when a mendicant does not identify with the eye, does not identify regarding the eye, does not identify as the eye, and does not identify ‘the eye is mine.’*";
P_HTM[577]="*Rūpe na maññati, rūpesu na maññati, rūpato na maññati, rūpā meti na maññati.**They don’t identify with sights, they don’t identify regarding sights, they don’t identify as sights, and they don’t identify ‘sights are mine.’*";
P_HTM[578]="*Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ na maññati, cakkhuviññāṇasmiṃ na maññati, cakkhuviññāṇato na maññati, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ meti na maññati.**They don’t identify with eye consciousness …*";
P_HTM[579]="*Cakkhusamphassaṃ na maññati, cakkhusamphassasmiṃ na maññati, cakkhusamphassato na maññati, cakkhusamphasso meti na maññati.**eye contact …*";
P_HTM[580]="*Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi na maññati, tasmimpi na maññati, tatopi na maññati, taṃ meti na maññati … pe …**They don’t identify with the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact. They don’t identify regarding that, they don’t identify as that, and they don’t identify ‘that is mine.’*";
P_HTM[581]="*jivhaṃ na maññati, jivhāya na maññati, jivhāto na maññati, jivhā meti na maññati.**They don’t identify with the ear … nose … tongue …*";
P_HTM[582]="*Rase na maññati, rasesu na maññati, rasato na maññati, rasā meti na maññati.* **";
P_HTM[583]="*Jivhāviññāṇaṃ na maññati, jivhāviññāṇasmiṃ na maññati, jivhāviññāṇato na maññati, jivhāviññāṇaṃ meti na maññati.* **";
P_HTM[584]="*Jivhāsamphassaṃ na maññati, jivhāsamphassasmiṃ na maññati, jivhāsamphassato na maññati, jivhāsamphasso meti na maññati.* **";
P_HTM[585]="*Yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi na maññati, tasmimpi na maññati, tatopi na maññati, taṃ meti na maññati … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[586]="*manaṃ na maññati, manasmiṃ na maññati, manato na maññati, mano meti na maññati.**mind …*";
P_HTM[587]="*Dhamme na maññati, dhammesu na maññati, dhammato na maññati, dhammā meti na maññati.* **";
P_HTM[588]="*Manoviññāṇaṃ na maññati, manoviññāṇasmiṃ na maññati, manoviññāṇato na maññati, manoviññāṇaṃ meti na maññati.* **";
P_HTM[589]="*Manosamphassaṃ na maññati, manosamphassasmiṃ na maññati, manosamphassato na maññati, manosamphasso meti na maññati.* **";
P_HTM[590]="*Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi na maññati, tasmimpi na maññati, tatopi na maññati, taṃ meti na maññati.**They don’t identify with the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact. They don’t identify regarding that, they don’t identify as that, and they don’t identify ‘that is mine.’*";
P_HTM[591]="*Sabbaṃ na maññati, sabbasmiṃ na maññati, sabbato na maññati, sabbaṃ meti na maññati.**They don’t identify with all, they don’t identify regarding all, they don’t identify as all, and they don’t identify ‘all is mine.’*";
P_HTM[592]="*So evaṃ amaññamāno na ca kiñci loke upādiyati.**Not identifying, they don’t grasp at anything in the world.*";
P_HTM[593]="*Anupādiyaṃ na paritassati. Aparitassaṃ paccattaññeva parinibbāyati.**Not grasping, they’re not anxious. Not being anxious, they personally become extinguished.*";
P_HTM[594]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[595]="*Ayaṃ kho sā, bhikkhave, sabbamaññitasamugghātasāruppā paṭipadā”ti.**This is the practice fit for uprooting all identifying.”*";
P_HTM[596]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[597]="*9. Paṭhamasamugghātasappāyasuttaṃ**The Practice Conducive to Uprooting (1st)*";
P_HTM[598]="*“Sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, paṭipadaṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all identifying.*";
P_HTM[599]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[600]="*Katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyā paṭipadā?**And what is the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all identifying?*";
P_HTM[601]="*Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhuṃ na maññati, cakkhusmiṃ na maññati, cakkhuto na maññati, cakkhuṃ meti na maññati.**It’s when a mendicant does not identify with the eye, does not identify in the eye, does not identify from the eye, and does not identify: ‘The eye is mine.’*";
P_HTM[602]="*Rūpe na maññati … pe …**They don’t identify with sights …*";
P_HTM[603]="*cakkhuviññāṇaṃ na maññati, cakkhusamphassaṃ na maññati, yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi na maññati, tasmimpi na maññati, tatopi na maññati, taṃ meti na maññati.**eye consciousness … eye contact. And they don’t identify with the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact. They don’t identify in that, they don’t identify from that, and they don’t identify: ‘That is mine.’*";
P_HTM[604]="*Yañhi, bhikkhave, maññati, yasmiṃ maññati, yato maññati, yaṃ meti maññati, tato taṃ hoti aññathā.**For whatever you identify with, whatever you identify in, whatever you identify as, and whatever you identify as ‘mine’: that becomes something else.*";
P_HTM[605]="*Aññathābhāvī bhavasatto loko bhavamevābhinandati … pe …**The world is attached to being, taking pleasure only in being, yet it becomes something else.*";
P_HTM[606]="*jivhaṃ na maññati, jivhāya na maññati, jivhāto na maññati, jivhā meti na maññati.**They don’t identify with the ear … nose … tongue …*";
P_HTM[607]="*Rase na maññati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[608]="*jivhāviññāṇaṃ na maññati, jivhāsamphassaṃ na maññati.* **";
P_HTM[609]="*Yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi na maññati, tasmimpi na maññati, tatopi na maññati, taṃ meti na maññati.* **";
P_HTM[610]="*Yañhi, bhikkhave, maññati, yasmiṃ maññati, yato maññati, yaṃ meti maññati, tato taṃ hoti aññathā.* **";
P_HTM[611]="*Aññathābhāvī bhavasatto loko bhavamevābhinandati … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[612]="*manaṃ na maññati, manasmiṃ na maññati, manato na maññati, mano meti na maññati.**mind …*";
P_HTM[613]="*Dhamme na maññati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[614]="*manoviññāṇaṃ na maññati, manosamphassaṃ na maññati.* **";
P_HTM[615]="*Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi na maññati, tasmimpi na maññati, tatopi na maññati, taṃ meti na maññati.**They don’t identify with the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact. They don’t identify in that, they don’t identify from that, and they don’t identify: ‘That is mine.’*";
P_HTM[616]="*Yañhi, bhikkhave, maññati, yasmiṃ maññati, yato maññati, yaṃ meti maññati, tato taṃ hoti aññathā.**For whatever you identify with, whatever you identify in, whatever you identify as, and whatever you identify as ‘mine’: that becomes something else.*";
P_HTM[617]="*Aññathābhāvī bhavasatto loko bhavamevābhinandati.**The world is attached to being, taking pleasure only in being, yet it becomes something else.*";
P_HTM[618]="*Yāvatā, bhikkhave, khandhadhātuāyatanaṃ tampi na maññati, tasmimpi na maññati, tatopi na maññati, taṃ meti na maññati.**As far as the aggregates, elements, and sense fields extend, they don’t identify with that, they don’t identify in that, they don’t identify from that, and they don’t identify: ‘That is mine.’*";
P_HTM[619]="*So evaṃ amaññamāno na ca kiñci loke upādiyati.**Not identifying, they don’t grasp at anything in the world.*";
P_HTM[620]="*Anupādiyaṃ na paritassati. Aparitassaṃ paccattaññeva parinibbāyati.**Not grasping, they’re not anxious. Not being anxious, they personally become extinguished.*";
P_HTM[621]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[622]="*Ayaṃ kho sā, bhikkhave, sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyā paṭipadā”ti.**This is the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all identifying.”*";
P_HTM[623]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[624]="*10. Dutiyasamugghātasappāyasuttaṃ**The Practice Conducive to Uprooting (2nd)*";
P_HTM[625]="*“Sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, paṭipadaṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all identifying.*";
P_HTM[626]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[627]="*Katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyā paṭipadā?**And what is the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all identifying?*";
P_HTM[628]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[629]="*cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[630]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[631]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[632]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[633]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[634]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[635]="*“No hetaṃ bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[636]="*“Rūpā … pe …**“Are sights …*";
P_HTM[637]="*cakkhuviññāṇaṃ …**eye consciousness …*";
P_HTM[638]="*cakkhusamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**eye contact …*";
P_HTM[639]="*“Anicco, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[640]="*“Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact: is that permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[641]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[642]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[643]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[644]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[645]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[646]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante” … pe ….**“No, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[647]="*“Jivhā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**“Is the ear … nose … tongue …*";
P_HTM[648]="*“Aniccā, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[649]="*“Rasā …* **";
P_HTM[650]="*jivhāviññāṇaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[651]="*jivhāsamphasso … pe …* **";
P_HTM[652]="*yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[653]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …* **";
P_HTM[654]="*dhammā …**body … mind …*";
P_HTM[655]="*manoviññāṇaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[656]="*manosamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[657]="*“Anicco, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[658]="*“Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**The pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact: is that permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[659]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[660]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[661]="*“Dukkhaṃ bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[662]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[663]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[664]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[665]="*“Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati.**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact.*";
P_HTM[666]="*Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati … pe …**And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact.*";
P_HTM[667]="*jivhāyapi nibbindati, rasesupi … pe … yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati … pe ….**They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[668]="*Manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati, manosamphassepi nibbindati.**They grow disillusioned with the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact.*";
P_HTM[669]="*Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati.**And they grow disillusioned with the painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact.*";
P_HTM[670]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[671]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’*";
P_HTM[672]="*Ayaṃ kho sā, bhikkhave, sabbamaññitasamugghātasappāyā paṭipadā”ti.**This is the practice that’s conducive to uprooting all identifying.”*";
P_HTM[673]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[674]="*Sabbavaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[675]="*Sabbañca dvepi pahānā,* **";
P_HTM[676]="*parijānāpare duve;* **";
P_HTM[677]="*Ādittaṃ addhabhūtañca,* **";
P_HTM[678]="*sāruppā dve ca sappāyā;* **";
P_HTM[679]="*Vaggo tena pavuccatīti.* **";
P_HTM[680]="*4. Jātidhammavaggo**Jātidhammavagga*";
P_HTM[681]="*1-10. Jātidhammādisuttadasakaṃ**33–42. Jātidhammādisuttadasaka*";
P_HTM[682]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[683]="*Tatra kho … pe …* **";
P_HTM[684]="*“sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, jātidhammaṃ.**“Mendicants, all is liable to be reborn.*";
P_HTM[685]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ jātidhammaṃ?**And what is the all that is liable to be reborn?*";
P_HTM[686]="*Cakkhu, bhikkhave, jātidhammaṃ.**The eye,*";
P_HTM[687]="*Rūpā …**sights,*";
P_HTM[688]="*cakkhuviññāṇaṃ …**eye consciousness,*";
P_HTM[689]="*cakkhusamphasso jātidhammo.**and eye contact are liable to be reborn.*";
P_HTM[690]="*Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi jātidhammaṃ … pe …**And the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact is also liable to be reborn.*";
P_HTM[691]="*jivhā …**The ear … nose … tongue …*";
P_HTM[692]="*rasā …* **";
P_HTM[693]="*jivhāviññāṇaṃ …* **";
P_HTM[694]="*jivhāsamphasso …* **";
P_HTM[695]="*yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi jātidhammaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[696]="*Kāyo … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[697]="*mano jātidhammo, dhammā jātidhammā, manoviññāṇaṃ jātidhammaṃ, manosamphasso jātidhammo.**The mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact are liable to be reborn.*";
P_HTM[698]="*Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi jātidhammaṃ.**And the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact is also liable to be reborn.*";
P_HTM[699]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi … cakkhuviññāṇepi … cakkhusamphassepi … pe …**Seeing this a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned …*";
P_HTM[700]="*nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[701]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[702]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, jarādhammaṃ …**“Mendicants, all is liable to grow old. …”*";
P_HTM[703]="*saṅkhittaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[704]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[705]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, byādhidhammaṃ …**“Mendicants, all is liable to fall sick. …”*";
P_HTM[706]="*saṅkhittaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[707]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[708]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, maraṇadhammaṃ …**“Mendicants, all is liable to die. …”*";
P_HTM[709]="*saṅkhittaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[710]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[711]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, sokadhammaṃ …**“Mendicants, all is liable to sorrow. …”*";
P_HTM[712]="*saṅkhittaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[713]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[714]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, saṅkilesikadhammaṃ …**“Mendicants, all is liable to be corrupted. …”*";
P_HTM[715]="*saṅkhittaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[716]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[717]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, khayadhammaṃ …**“Mendicants, all is liable to end. …”*";
P_HTM[718]="*saṅkhittaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[719]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[720]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, vayadhammaṃ …**“Mendicants, all is liable to vanish. …”*";
P_HTM[721]="*saṅkhittaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[722]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[723]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, samudayadhammaṃ …**“Mendicants, all is liable to originate. …”*";
P_HTM[724]="*saṅkhittaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[725]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[726]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, nirodhadhammaṃ …**“Mendicants, all is liable to cease. …”*";
P_HTM[727]="*saṅkhittaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[728]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[729]="*Jātidhammavaggo catuttho.* **";
P_HTM[730]="*Jātijarābyādhimaraṇaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[731]="*Soko ca saṅkilesikaṃ;* **";
P_HTM[732]="*Khayavayasamudayaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[733]="*Nirodhadhammena te dasāti.* **";
P_HTM[734]="*5. Sabbaaniccavaggo**Sabbaaniccavagga*";
P_HTM[735]="*1-9. Aniccādisuttanavakaṃ**43–51. Aniccādisuttanavaka*";
P_HTM[736]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[737]="*Tatra kho … pe …* **";
P_HTM[738]="*“sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ.**“Mendicants, all is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[739]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ aniccaṃ?**And what is the all that is impermanent?*";
P_HTM[740]="*Cakkhu, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ, rūpā aniccā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ, cakkhusamphasso anicco.**The eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact are impermanent.*";
P_HTM[741]="*Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccaṃ … pe …**And the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact is also impermanent.*";
P_HTM[742]="*jivhā aniccā, rasā aniccā, jivhāviññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ, jivhāsamphasso anicco.**The ear … nose … tongue …*";
P_HTM[743]="*Yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[744]="*Kāyo anicco … pe …**body …*";
P_HTM[745]="*mano anicco, dhammā aniccā, manoviññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ, manosamphasso anicco.**The mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact are impermanent.*";
P_HTM[746]="*Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi aniccaṃ.**The painful, pleasant, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact is also impermanent.*";
P_HTM[747]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati.**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned …*";
P_HTM[748]="*Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[749]="*manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati, manosamphassepi nibbindati,* **";
P_HTM[750]="*yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati.* **";
P_HTM[751]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[752]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[753]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[754]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ … pe ….**“Mendicants, all is suffering. …”*";
P_HTM[755]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[756]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, anattā … pe ….**“Mendicants, all is not-self. …”*";
P_HTM[757]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[758]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, abhiññeyyaṃ … pe ….**“Mendicants, all is to be directly known. …”*";
P_HTM[759]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[760]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, pariññeyyaṃ … pe ….**“Mendicants, all is to be completely understood. …”*";
P_HTM[761]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[762]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, pahātabbaṃ … pe ….**“Mendicants, all is to be given up. …”*";
P_HTM[763]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[764]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, sacchikātabbaṃ … pe ….**“Mendicants, all is to be realized. …”*";
P_HTM[765]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[766]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, abhiññāpariññeyyaṃ … pe ….**“Mendicants, all is to be directly known and completely understood. …”*";
P_HTM[767]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[768]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, upaddutaṃ … pe ….**“Mendicants, all is troubled. …”*";
P_HTM[769]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[770]="*10. Upassaṭṭhasuttaṃ**Disturbed*";
P_HTM[771]="*“Sabbaṃ, bhikkhave, upassaṭṭhaṃ.**“Mendicants, all is disturbed.*";
P_HTM[772]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, sabbaṃ upassaṭṭhaṃ?**And what is the all that is disturbed?*";
P_HTM[773]="*Cakkhu, bhikkhave, upassaṭṭhaṃ, rūpā upassaṭṭhā, cakkhuviññāṇaṃ upassaṭṭhaṃ, cakkhusamphasso upassaṭṭho.**The eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact are disturbed.*";
P_HTM[774]="*Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi upassaṭṭhaṃ … pe …**And the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by eye contact is also disturbed.*";
P_HTM[775]="*jivhā upassaṭṭhā, rasā upassaṭṭhā, jivhāviññāṇaṃ upassaṭṭhaṃ, jivhāsamphasso upassaṭṭho.**The ear … nose … tongue …*";
P_HTM[776]="*Yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi upassaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[777]="*Kāyo upassaṭṭho …**body …*";
P_HTM[778]="*mano upassaṭṭho, dhammā upassaṭṭhā, manoviññāṇaṃ upassaṭṭhaṃ, manosamphasso upassaṭṭho.**The mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact are disturbed.*";
P_HTM[779]="*Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tampi upassaṭṭhaṃ.**And the pleasant, painful, or neutral feeling that arises conditioned by mind contact is also disturbed.*";
P_HTM[780]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati.**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned …*";
P_HTM[781]="*Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[782]="*manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati, manosamphassepi nibbindati.* **";
P_HTM[783]="*Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedayitaṃ sukhaṃ vā dukkhaṃ vā adukkhamasukhaṃ vā tasmimpi nibbindati.* **";
P_HTM[784]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.* **";
P_HTM[785]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[786]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[787]="*Sabbaaniccavaggo pañcamo.* **";
P_HTM[788]="*Aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ anattā,* **";
