P_HTM[880]="*8. Sabbupādānapariññāsuttaṃ**The Complete Understanding of All Grasping*";
P_HTM[881]="*“Sabbupādānapariññāya vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the principle for the complete understanding of all grasping.*";
P_HTM[882]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[883]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariññāya dhammo?**And what is the principle for the complete understanding of all grasping?*";
P_HTM[884]="*Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso.**Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[885]="*Phassapaccayā vedanā.**Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[886]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati, vedanāyapi nibbindati.**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, and feeling.*";
P_HTM[887]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimokkhā ‘pariññātaṃ me upādānan’ti pajānāti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they are released, they understand: ‘I have completely understood grasping.’*";
P_HTM[888]="*Sotañca paṭicca sadde ca uppajjati …**Ear consciousness arises dependent on the ear and sounds. …*";
P_HTM[889]="*ghānañca paṭicca gandhe ca …**Nose consciousness arises dependent on the nose and smells. …*";
P_HTM[890]="*jivhañca paṭicca rase ca …**Tongue consciousness arises dependent on the tongue and tastes. …*";
P_HTM[891]="*kāyañca paṭicca phoṭṭhabbe ca …**Body consciousness arises dependent on the body and touches. …*";
P_HTM[892]="*manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso.**Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[893]="*Phassapaccayā vedanā.**Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[894]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati, manosamphassepi nibbindati, vedanāyapi nibbindati.**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, mind contact, and feeling.*";
P_HTM[895]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimokkhā ‘pariññātaṃ me upādānan’ti pajānāti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they are released, they understand: ‘I have completely understood grasping.’*";
P_HTM[896]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariññāya dhammo”ti.**This is the principle for the complete understanding of all grasping.”*";
P_HTM[897]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[898]="*9. Paṭhamasabbupādānapariyādānasuttaṃ**The Depletion of All Fuel (1st)*";
P_HTM[899]="*“Sabbupādānapariyādānāya vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the principle for depleting all fuel.*";
P_HTM[900]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[901]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariyādānāya dhammo?**And what is the principle for depleting all fuel?*";
P_HTM[902]="*Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso.**Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[903]="*Phassapaccayā vedanā.**Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[904]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati, vedanāyapi nibbindati.**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, eye contact, and feeling.*";
P_HTM[905]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimokkhā ‘pariyādinnaṃ me upādānan’ti pajānāti … pe …**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they are released, they understand: ‘I have completely depleted grasping.’*";
P_HTM[906]="*jivhañca paṭicca rase ca uppajjati jivhāviññāṇaṃ … pe …**Ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[907]="*manañca paṭicca dhamme ca uppajjati manoviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso.**Mind consciousness arises dependent on the mind and thoughts. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[908]="*Phassapaccayā vedanā.**Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[909]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati manosamphassepi nibbindati, vedanāyapi nibbindati.**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, mind contact, and feeling.*";
P_HTM[910]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimokkhā ‘pariyādinnaṃ me upādānan’ti pajānāti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they are released, they understand: ‘I have completely depleted grasping.’*";
P_HTM[911]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariyādānāya dhammo”ti.**This is the principle for depleting all fuel.”*";
P_HTM[912]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[913]="*10. Dutiyasabbupādānapariyādānasuttaṃ**The Depletion of All Fuel (2nd)*";
P_HTM[914]="*“Sabbupādānapariyādānāya vo, bhikkhave, dhammaṃ desessāmi.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the principle for depleting all fuel.*";
P_HTM[915]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[916]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sabbupādānapariyādānāya dhammo?**And what is the principle for depleting all fuel?*";
P_HTM[917]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[918]="*cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[919]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[920]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[921]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[922]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[923]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[924]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
