P_HTM[2371]="*Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, lokassa samudayo.**This is the origin of the world.*";
P_HTM[2372]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, lokassa atthaṅgamo?**And what is the ending of the world?*";
P_HTM[2373]="*Cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso.**Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[2374]="*Phassapaccayā vedanā;**Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[2375]="*vedanāpaccayā taṇhā.**Feeling is a condition for craving.*";
P_HTM[2376]="*Tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodhā upādānanirodho;**When that craving fades away and ceases with nothing left over, grasping ceases.*";
P_HTM[2377]="*upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho;**When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases.*";
P_HTM[2378]="*bhavanirodhā jātinirodho;**When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases.*";
P_HTM[2379]="*jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti.**When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress cease.*";
P_HTM[2380]="*Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.*";
