P_HTM[2390]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2391]="*5. Seyyohamasmisuttaṃ**I’m Better*";
P_HTM[2392]="*“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati kiṃ upādāya kiṃ abhinivissa seyyohamasmīti vā hoti, sadisohamasmīti vā hoti, hīnohamasmīti vā hotī”ti?**“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, do people think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’?”*";
P_HTM[2393]="*“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe ….**“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”*";
P_HTM[2394]="*“Cakkhusmiṃ kho, bhikkhave, sati cakkhuṃ upādāya cakkhuṃ abhinivissa seyyohamasmīti vā hoti, sadisohamasmīti vā hoti, hīnohamasmīti vā hoti … pe …**“When there’s an eye, because of grasping the eye and insisting on the eye, people think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’. …*";
P_HTM[2395]="*jivhāya sati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2396]="*manasmiṃ sati manaṃ upādāya manaṃ abhinivissa seyyohamasmīti vā hoti, sadisohamasmīti vā hoti, hīnohamasmīti vā hoti.**When there’s a mind, because of grasping the mind and insisting on the mind, people think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’.*";
P_HTM[2397]="*Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave,**What do you think, mendicants?*";
P_HTM[2398]="*cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[2399]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2400]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[2401]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2402]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya seyyohamasmīti vā assa, sadisohamasmīti vā assa, hīnohamasmīti vā assā”ti?**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would people think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’?”*";
P_HTM[2403]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante” … pe …**“No, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[2404]="*jivhā …* **";
P_HTM[2405]="*niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2406]="*“Aniccā, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2407]="*“Mano nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**“Is the mind permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[2408]="*“Anicco, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2409]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[2410]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2411]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya seyyohamasmīti vā assa, sadisohamasmīti vā assa, hīnohamasmīti vā assā”ti?**“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would people think ‘I’m better’ or ‘I’m equal’ or ‘I’m worse’?”*";
P_HTM[2412]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2413]="*“Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati … pe … manasmimpi nibbindati.**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind.*";
P_HTM[2414]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[2415]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[2416]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2417]="*6. Saṃyojaniyasuttaṃ**Things Prone to Being Fettered*";
P_HTM[2418]="*“Saṃyojaniye ca, bhikkhave, dhamme desessāmi saṃyojanañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the things that are prone to being fettered, and the fetter.*";
P_HTM[2419]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[2420]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyā dhammā, katamañca saṃyojanaṃ?**What are the things that are prone to being fettered? And what is the fetter?*";
P_HTM[2421]="*Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyo dhammo.**The eye is something that’s prone to being fettered.*";
P_HTM[2422]="*Yo tattha chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ … pe …**The desire and greed for it is the fetter.*";
P_HTM[2423]="*jivhā saṃyojaniyo dhammo … pe …**The ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[2424]="*mano saṃyojaniyo dhammo.**mind is something that’s prone to being fettered.*";
P_HTM[2425]="*Yo tattha chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ.**The desire and greed for it is the fetter.*";
P_HTM[2426]="*Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyā dhammā, idaṃ saṃyojanan”ti.**These are called the things that are prone to being fettered, and this is the fetter.”*";
P_HTM[2427]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2428]="*7. Upādāniyasuttaṃ**Things Prone to Being Grasped*";
P_HTM[2429]="*“Upādāniye ca, bhikkhave, dhamme desessāmi upādānañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the things that are prone to being grasped, and the grasping.*";
P_HTM[2430]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[2431]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, upādāniyā dhammā, katamañca upādānaṃ?**What are the things that are prone to being grasped? And what is the grasping?*";
P_HTM[2432]="*Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, upādāniyo dhammo.**The eye is something that’s prone to being grasped.*";
P_HTM[2433]="*Yo tattha chandarāgo, taṃ tattha upādānaṃ … pe …**The desire and greed for it is the grasping.*";
P_HTM[2434]="*jivhā upādāniyo dhammo … pe …**The ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[2435]="*mano upādāniyo dhammo.**mind is something that’s prone to being grasped.*";
P_HTM[2436]="*Yo tattha chandarāgo, taṃ tattha upādānaṃ.**The desire and greed for it is the grasping.*";
P_HTM[2437]="*Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, upādāniyā dhammā, idaṃ upādānan”ti.**These are called the things that are prone to being grasped, and this is the grasping.”*";
P_HTM[2438]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2439]="*8. Ajjhattikāyatanaparijānanasuttaṃ**Complete Understanding of the Interior*";
P_HTM[2440]="*“Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**“Mendicants, without directly knowing and completely understanding the eye, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[2441]="*Sotaṃ …**Without directly knowing and completely understanding the ear …*";
P_HTM[2442]="*ghānaṃ …**nose …*";
P_HTM[2443]="*jivhaṃ …**tongue …*";
P_HTM[2444]="*kāyaṃ …**body …*";
P_HTM[2445]="*manaṃ anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**mind, without dispassion for it and giving it up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[2446]="*Cakkhuñca kho, bhikkhave, abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya … pe …**By directly knowing and completely understanding the eye, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering.*";
P_HTM[2447]="*jivhaṃ …**By directly knowing and completely understanding the ear … nose … tongue …*";
P_HTM[2448]="*kāyaṃ …**body …*";
P_HTM[2449]="*manaṃ abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāyā”ti.**mind, having dispassion for it and giving it up, you can end suffering.”*";
P_HTM[2450]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2451]="*9. Bāhirāyatanaparijānanasuttaṃ**Complete Understanding of the Exterior*";
P_HTM[2452]="*“Rūpe, bhikkhave, anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**“Mendicants, without directly knowing and completely understanding sights …*";
P_HTM[2453]="*Sadde …**sounds …*";
P_HTM[2454]="*gandhe …**smells …*";
P_HTM[2455]="*rase …**tastes …*";
P_HTM[2456]="*phoṭṭhabbe …**touches …*";
P_HTM[2457]="*dhamme anabhijānaṃ aparijānaṃ avirājayaṃ appajahaṃ abhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**thoughts, without dispassion for them and giving them up, you can’t end suffering.*";
P_HTM[2458]="*Rūpe ca kho, bhikkhave, abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāya.**By directly knowing and completely understanding sights …*";
P_HTM[2459]="*Sadde …**sounds …*";
P_HTM[2460]="*gandhe …**smells …*";
P_HTM[2461]="*rase …**tastes …*";
P_HTM[2462]="*phoṭṭhabbe …**touches …*";
P_HTM[2463]="*dhamme abhijānaṃ parijānaṃ virājayaṃ pajahaṃ bhabbo dukkhakkhayāyā”ti.**thoughts, having dispassion for them and giving them up, you can end suffering.”*";
P_HTM[2464]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2465]="*10. Upassutisuttaṃ**Listening In*";
P_HTM[2466]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā nātike viharati giñjakāvasathe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Nādika in the brick house.*";
P_HTM[2467]="*Atha kho bhagavā rahogato paṭisallīno imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ abhāsi:**Then while the Buddha was in private retreat he spoke this exposition of the teaching:*";
P_HTM[2468]="*“cakkhuñca paṭicca rūpe ca uppajjati cakkhuviññāṇaṃ. Tiṇṇaṃ saṅgati phasso.**“Eye consciousness arises dependent on the eye and sights. The meeting of the three is contact.*";
P_HTM[2469]="*Phassapaccayā vedanā;**Contact is a condition for feeling.*";
P_HTM[2470]="*vedanāpaccayā taṇhā;**Feeling is a condition for craving.*";
P_HTM[2471]="*taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ;**Craving is a condition for grasping.*";
P_HTM[2472]="*upādānapaccayā bhavo;**Grasping is a condition for continued existence.*";
P_HTM[2473]="*bhavapaccayā jāti;**Continued existence is a condition for rebirth.*";
P_HTM[2474]="*jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti.**Rebirth is a condition that gives rise to old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress.*";
P_HTM[2475]="*Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti.**That is how this entire mass of suffering originates.*";
