P_HTM[2500]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu bhagavato upassuti ṭhito hoti.**Now at that time a certain monk was standing listening in on the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2501]="*Addasā kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ upassuti ṭhitaṃ.**The Buddha saw him*";
P_HTM[2502]="*Disvāna taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca:**and said,*";
P_HTM[2503]="*“assosi no tvaṃ, bhikkhu, imaṃ dhammapariyāyan”ti?**“Monk, did you hear that exposition of the teaching?”*";
P_HTM[2504]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2505]="*“Uggaṇhāhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ.**“Learn that exposition of the teaching,*";
P_HTM[2506]="*Pariyāpuṇāhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ.**memorize it,*";
P_HTM[2507]="*Dhārehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ.**and remember it.*";
P_HTM[2508]="*Atthasañhitoyaṃ, bhikkhu, dhammapariyāyo ādibrahmacariyako”ti.**That exposition of the teaching is beneficial and relates to the fundamentals of the spiritual life.”*";
P_HTM[2509]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2510]="*Yogakkhemivaggo paṭhamo.* **";
P_HTM[2511]="*Yogakkhemi upādāya,* **";
P_HTM[2512]="*Dukkhaṃ loko ca seyyo ca;* **";
P_HTM[2513]="*Saṃyojanaṃ upādānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2514]="*Dve parijānaṃ upassutīti.* **";
P_HTM[2515]="*12. Lokakāmaguṇavaggo**The World and the Kinds of Sensual Stimulation*";
P_HTM[2516]="*1. Paṭhamamārapāsasuttaṃ**Māra’s Snare (1st)*";
P_HTM[2517]="*“Santi, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**“Mendicants, there are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2518]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati—**If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2519]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āvāsagato mārassa, mārassa vasaṃ gato, paṭimukkassa mārapāso.**they’re called a mendicant trapped in Māra’s lair, fallen under Māra’s sway, and caught in Māra’s snare.*";
P_HTM[2520]="*Baddho so mārabandhanena yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe ….**They’re bound by Māra’s bonds, and the Wicked One can do what he wants with them.*";
P_HTM[2521]="*Santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …*";
P_HTM[2522]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati—* **";
P_HTM[2523]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āvāsagato mārassa, mārassa vasaṃ gato, paṭimukkassa mārapāso. Baddho so mārabandhanena … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2524]="*Santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2525]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati—**If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keep clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2526]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu āvāsagato mārassa, mārassa vasaṃ gato, paṭimukkassa mārapāso.**they’re called a mendicant trapped in Māra’s lair, fallen under Māra’s sway, and caught in Māra’s snare.*";
P_HTM[2527]="*Baddho so mārabandhanena yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe …**They’re bound by Māra, and the Wicked One can do what he wants with them.*";
P_HTM[2528]="*Santi ca kho, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2529]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati—**If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2530]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu nāvāsagato mārassa, na mārassa vasaṃ gato, ummukkassa mārapāso.**they’re called a mendicant not trapped in Māra’s lair, not fallen under Māra’s sway, and released from Māra’s snare.*";
P_HTM[2531]="*Mutto so mārabandhanena na yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe ….**They’re free from Māra’s bonds, and the Wicked One cannot do what he wants with them.*";
P_HTM[2532]="*Santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …*";
P_HTM[2533]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati—* **";
P_HTM[2534]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu nāvāsagato mārassa, na mārassa vasaṃ gato, ummukkassa mārapāso. Mutto so mārabandhanena na yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2535]="*Santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2536]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati—**If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2537]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu nāvāsagato mārassa, na mārassa vasaṃ gato, ummukkassa mārapāso.**they’re called a mendicant not trapped in Māra’s lair, not fallen under Māra’s sway, and released from Māra’s snare.*";
P_HTM[2538]="*Mutto so mārabandhanena na yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato”ti.**They’re free from Māra’s bonds, and the Wicked One cannot do what he wants with them.”*";
P_HTM[2539]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2540]="*2. Dutiyamārapāsasuttaṃ**Māra’s Snare (2nd)*";
P_HTM[2541]="*“Santi, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**“Mendicants, there are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2542]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati—**If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2543]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu baddho cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu, āvāsagato mārassa, mārassa vasaṃ gato, paṭimukkassa mārapāso.**they’re called a mendicant who is bound when it comes to sights known by the eye. They’re trapped in Māra’s lair, fallen under Māra’s sway, and caught in Māra’s snare.*";
P_HTM[2544]="*Baddho so mārabandhanena yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe ….**They’re bound by Māra’s bonds, and the Wicked One can do what he wants with them.*";
P_HTM[2545]="*Santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …**There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …*";
P_HTM[2546]="*santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2547]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati—**If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2548]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu baddho manoviññeyyesu dhammesu, āvāsagato mārassa, mārassa vasaṃ gato, paṭimukkassa mārapāso.**they’re called a mendicant who is bound when it comes to thoughts known by the mind. They’re trapped in Māra’s lair, fallen under Māra’s sway, and caught in Māra’s snare.*";
P_HTM[2549]="*Baddho so mārabandhanena yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe ….**They’re bound by Māra’s bonds, and the Wicked One can do what he wants with them.*";
P_HTM[2550]="*Santi ca kho, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2551]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati—**If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2552]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mutto cakkhuviññeyyehi rūpehi, nāvāsagato mārassa, na mārassa vasaṃ gato, ummukkassa mārapāso.**they’re called a mendicant not trapped in Māra’s lair, not fallen under Māra’s sway, and released from Māra’s snare.*";
P_HTM[2553]="*Mutto so mārabandhanena na yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe ….**They’re free from Māra’s bonds, and the Wicked One cannot do what he wants with them.*";
P_HTM[2554]="*Santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …**There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …*";
P_HTM[2555]="*santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2556]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati—**If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2557]="*ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu mutto manoviññeyyehi dhammehi, nāvāsagato mārassa, na mārassa vasaṃ gato, ummukkassa mārapāso.**they’re called a mendicant not trapped in Māra’s lair, not fallen under Māra’s sway, and released from Māra’s snare.*";
P_HTM[2558]="*Mutto so mārabandhanena na yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato”ti.**They’re free from Māra’s bonds, and the Wicked One cannot do what he wants with them.”*";
P_HTM[2559]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2560]="*3. Lokantagamanasuttaṃ**Traveling to the End of the World*";
P_HTM[2561]="*“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti vadāmi.**“Mendicants, I say it’s not possible to know or see or reach the end of the world by traveling.*";
P_HTM[2562]="*Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmī”ti.**But I also say there’s no making an end of suffering without reaching the end of the world.”*";
P_HTM[2563]="*Idaṃ vatvā bhagavā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi.**When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his dwelling.*";
P_HTM[2564]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:**Soon after the Buddha left, those mendicants considered,*";
P_HTM[2565]="*“idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṃkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**“The Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail. …*";
P_HTM[2566]="*‘“nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyan”ti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2567]="*Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2568]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṃkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā”ti?**Who can explain in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[2569]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi:**Then those mendicants thought,*";
P_HTM[2570]="*“ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**“This Venerable Ānanda is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[2571]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.**He is capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2572]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā”ti.**Let’s go to him, and ask him about this matter.”*";
P_HTM[2573]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu.**Then those mendicants went to Ānanda and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[2574]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side. They told him what had happened, and said,*";
P_HTM[2575]="*“Idaṃ kho no, āvuso ānanda, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[2576]="*‘nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2577]="*Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2578]="*Tesaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2579]="*‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho—* **";
P_HTM[2580]="*nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2581]="*Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmīti.* **";
P_HTM[2582]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2583]="*Tesaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2584]="*‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2585]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2586]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2587]="*Vibhajatāyasmā ānando”ti.**“May Venerable Ānanda please explain this.”*";
P_HTM[2588]="*“Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa tiṭṭhato sāravato atikkammeva, mūlaṃ atikkammeva, khandhaṃ sākhāpalāse sāraṃ pariyesitabbaṃ maññeyya;**“Reverends, suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. And while wandering in search of heartwood he’d come across a large tree standing with heartwood. But he’d pass over the roots and trunk, imagining that the heartwood should be sought in the branches and leaves.*";
P_HTM[2589]="*evaṃ sampadamidaṃ āyasmantānaṃ satthari sammukhībhūte taṃ bhagavantaṃ atisitvā amhe etamatthaṃ paṭipucchitabbaṃ maññatha.**Such is the consequence for the venerables. Though you were face to face with the Buddha, you passed him by, imagining that you should ask me about this matter.*";
P_HTM[2590]="*So hāvuso, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti, passaṃ passati—**For he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is knowledge, he is the truth, he is supreme. He is the teacher, the proclaimer, the elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the lord of truth, the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[2591]="*cakkhubhūto, ñāṇabhūto, dhammabhūto, brahmabhūto, vattā, pavattā, atthassa ninnetā, amatassa dātā, dhammassāmī, tathāgato.* **";
P_HTM[2592]="*So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi yaṃ bhagavantaṃyeva etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha.**That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter.*";
P_HTM[2593]="*Yathā vo bhagavā byākareyya tathā vo dhāreyyāthā”ti.**You should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”*";
P_HTM[2594]="*“Addhāvuso ānanda, bhagavā jānaṃ jānāti, passaṃ passati—**“Certainly he is the Buddha, who knows and sees. He is vision, he is knowledge, he is the truth, he is supreme. He is the teacher, the proclaimer, the elucidator of meaning, the bestower of the deathless, the lord of truth, the Realized One.*";
P_HTM[2595]="*cakkhubhūto, ñāṇabhūto, dhammabhūto, brahmabhūto, vattā, pavattā, atthassa ninnetā, amatassa dātā, dhammassāmī, tathāgato.* **";
P_HTM[2596]="*So ceva panetassa kālo ahosi yaṃ bhagavantaṃyeva etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāma.**That was the time to approach the Buddha and ask about this matter.*";
P_HTM[2597]="*Yathā no bhagavā byākareyya tathā naṃ dhāreyyāma.**We should have remembered it in line with the Buddha’s answer.*";
P_HTM[2598]="*Api cāyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**Still, Venerable Ānanda is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[2599]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.**You are capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief passage for recitation given by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2600]="*Vibhajatāyasmā ānando agaruṃ karitvā”ti.**Please explain this, if it’s no trouble.”*";
P_HTM[2601]="*“Tenahāvuso, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Then listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[2602]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2603]="*Āyasmā ānando etadavoca:**Ānanda said this:*";
P_HTM[2604]="*“Yaṃ kho vo, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**“Reverends, the Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:*";
P_HTM[2605]="*‘nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti vadāmi.**‘Mendicants, I say it’s not possible to know or see or reach the end of the world by traveling.*";
P_HTM[2606]="*Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmī’ti,**But I also say there’s no making an end of suffering without reaching the end of the world.’*";
P_HTM[2607]="*imassa khvāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi.**This is how I understand the detailed meaning of this passage for recitation.*";
P_HTM[2608]="*Yena kho, āvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī—**Whatever in the world through which you perceive the world and conceive the world*";
P_HTM[2609]="*ayaṃ vuccati ariyassa vinaye loko.**is called the world in the training of the noble one.*";
P_HTM[2610]="*Kena cāvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī?**And through what in the world do you perceive the world and conceive the world?*";
P_HTM[2611]="*Cakkhunā kho, āvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī.**Through the eye in the world you perceive the world and conceive the world.*";
P_HTM[2612]="*Sotena kho, āvuso …**Through the ear …*";
P_HTM[2613]="*ghānena kho, āvuso …**nose …*";
P_HTM[2614]="*jivhāya kho, āvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī.**tongue …*";
P_HTM[2615]="*Kāyena kho, āvuso …**body …*";
P_HTM[2616]="*manena kho, āvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī.**mind in the world you perceive the world and conceive the world.*";
P_HTM[2617]="*Yena kho, āvuso, lokasmiṃ lokasaññī hoti lokamānī—**Whatever in the world through which you perceive the world and conceive the world*";
P_HTM[2618]="*ayaṃ vuccati ariyassa vinaye loko.**is called the world in the training of the noble one.*";
P_HTM[2619]="*Yaṃ kho vo, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**When the Buddha gave this brief passage for recitation, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:*";
P_HTM[2620]="*‘nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti vadāmi.**‘Mendicants, I say it’s not possible to know or see or reach the end of the world by traveling.*";
P_HTM[2621]="*Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmī’ti,**But I also say there’s no making an end of suffering without reaching the end of the world.’*";
P_HTM[2622]="*imassa khvāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi.**That is how I understand the detailed meaning of this summary.*";
P_HTM[2623]="*Ākaṅkhamānā ca pana tumhe āyasmanto bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha.**If you wish, you may go to the Buddha and ask him about this.*";
P_HTM[2624]="*Yathā vo bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**You should remember it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”*";
P_HTM[2625]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**“Yes, reverend,” replied those mendicants. Then they rose from their seats and went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2626]="*“Yaṃ kho no, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[2627]="*‘nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2628]="*Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2629]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2630]="*‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho—* **";
P_HTM[2631]="*nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, gamanena lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ, daṭṭheyyaṃ, patteyyanti vadāmi.* **";
P_HTM[2632]="*Na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appatvā lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmīti.* **";
P_HTM[2633]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2634]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2635]="*‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2636]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2637]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2638]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamimha; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipucchimha.* **";
P_HTM[2639]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, āyasmatā ānandena imehi ākārehi imehi padehi imehi byañjanehi attho vibhatto”ti.**Then they said, “And Ānanda explained the meaning to us in this manner, with these words and phrases.”*";
P_HTM[2640]="*“Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, ānando; mahāpañño, bhikkhave, ānando.**“Mendicants, Ānanda is astute, he has great wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2641]="*Mañcepi tumhe, bhikkhave, etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha, ahampi taṃ evamevaṃ byākareyyaṃ yathā taṃ ānandena byākataṃ.**If you came to me and asked this question, I would answer it in exactly the same way as Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[2642]="*Eso cevetassa attho, evañca naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**That is what it means, and that’s how you should remember it.”*";
P_HTM[2643]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2644]="*4. Kāmaguṇasuttaṃ**The Kinds of Sensual Stimulation*";
P_HTM[2645]="*“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi:**“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought:*";
P_HTM[2646]="*‘yeme pañca kāmaguṇā cetaso samphuṭṭhapubbā atītā niruddhā vipariṇatā, tatra me cittaṃ bahulaṃ gacchamānaṃ gaccheyya paccuppannesu vā appaṃ vā anāgatesu’.**‘My mind might often stray towards the five kinds of sensual stimulation that I formerly experienced—which have passed, ceased, and perished—or to those in the present, or in the future a little.’*";
P_HTM[2647]="*Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi:**Then it occurred to me:*";
P_HTM[2648]="*‘yeme pañca kāmaguṇā cetaso samphuṭṭhapubbā atītā niruddhā vipariṇatā, tatra me attarūpena appamādo sati cetaso ārakkho karaṇīyo’.**‘In my own way I should practice diligence, mindfulness, and protecting the mind regarding the five kinds of sensual stimulation that I formerly experienced—which have passed, ceased, and perished.’*";
P_HTM[2649]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, tumhākampi ye te pañca kāmaguṇā cetaso samphuṭṭhapubbā atītā niruddhā vipariṇatā, tatra vo cittaṃ bahulaṃ gacchamānaṃ gaccheyya paccuppannesu vā appaṃ vā anāgatesu.**So, mendicants, your minds might also often stray towards the five kinds of sensual stimulation that you formerly experienced—which have passed, ceased, and perished—or to those in the present, or in the future a little.*";
P_HTM[2650]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, tumhākampi ye te pañca kāmaguṇā cetaso samphuṭṭhapubbā atītā niruddhā vipariṇatā, tatra vo attarūpehi appamādo sati cetaso ārakkho karaṇīyo.**So in your own way you should practice diligence, mindfulness, and protecting the mind regarding the five kinds of sensual stimulation that I formerly experienced—which have passed, ceased, and perished.*";
P_HTM[2651]="*Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, se āyatane veditabbe yattha cakkhu ca nirujjhati, rūpasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …**So you should understand that dimension where the eye ceases and perception of sights fades away.*";
P_HTM[2652]="*yattha jivhā ca nirujjhati, rasasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …**You should understand that dimension where the ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[2653]="*yattha mano ca nirujjhati, dhammasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe”ti.**mind ceases and perception of thoughts fades away.”*";
P_HTM[2654]="*Idaṃ vatvā bhagavā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ pāvisi.**When he had spoken, the Holy One got up from his seat and entered his dwelling.*";
P_HTM[2655]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:**Soon after the Buddha left, those mendicants considered,*";
P_HTM[2656]="*“idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**“The Buddha gave this brief summary, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail. …*";
P_HTM[2657]="*‘tasmātiha, bhikkhave, se āyatane veditabbe yattha cakkhu ca nirujjhati, rūpasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2658]="*yattha jivhā ca nirujjhati, rasasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2659]="*yattha mano ca nirujjhati, dhammasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2660]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā”ti?**Who can explain in detail the meaning of this brief summary given by the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[2661]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi:**Then those mendicants thought,*";
P_HTM[2662]="*“ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.**“This Venerable Ānanda is praised by the Buddha and esteemed by his sensible spiritual companions.*";
P_HTM[2663]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.**He is capable of explaining in detail the meaning of this brief summary given by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2664]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā”ti.**Let’s go to him, and ask him about this matter.”*";
P_HTM[2665]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu.**Then those mendicants went to Ānanda, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[2666]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavocuṃ:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side. They told him what had happened, and said,*";
P_HTM[2667]="*“Idaṃ kho no, āvuso ānanda, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[2668]="*‘tasmātiha, bhikkhave, se āyatane veditabbe yattha cakkhu ca nirujjhati, rūpasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2669]="*yattha jivhā ca nirujjhati, rasasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2670]="*yattha mano ca nirujjhati, dhammasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2671]="*Tesaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2672]="*‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[2673]="*“tasmātiha, bhikkhave, se āyatane veditabbe yattha cakkhu ca nirujjhati, rūpasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2674]="*yattha jivhā ca nirujjhati, rasasaññā ca nirujjhati se āyatane veditabbe … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2675]="*yattha mano ca nirujjhati, dhammasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2676]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2677]="*Tesaṃ no, āvuso, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2678]="*‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2679]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2680]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2681]="*Vibhajatāyasmā ānando”ti.**“May Venerable Ānanda please explain this.”*";
P_HTM[2682]="*“Seyyathāpi, āvuso, puriso sāratthiko sāragavesī sārapariyesanaṃ caramāno mahato rukkhassa … pe …**“Reverends, suppose there was a person in need of heartwood. …”*";
P_HTM[2683]="*vibhajatāyasmā ānando agaruṃ karitvā”ti.**“Please explain this, if it’s no trouble.”*";
P_HTM[2684]="*“Tenahāvuso, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti.**“Then listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”*";
P_HTM[2685]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paccassosuṃ.**“Yes, reverend,” they replied.*";
P_HTM[2686]="*Āyasmā ānando etadavoca:**Ānanda said this:*";
P_HTM[2687]="*“Yaṃ kho vo, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**“Reverends, the Buddha gave this brief summary, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail:*";
P_HTM[2688]="*‘tasmātiha, bhikkhave, se āyatane veditabbe yattha cakkhu ca nirujjhati, rūpasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …**‘So you should understand that dimension where the eye ceases and perception of sights fades away. You should understand that dimension where the ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[2689]="*yattha mano ca nirujjhati, dhammasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe’ti.**mind ceases and perception of thoughts fades away.’*";
P_HTM[2690]="*Imassa khvāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi.**And this is how I understand the detailed meaning of this summary.*";
P_HTM[2691]="*Saḷāyatananirodhaṃ no etaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā sandhāya bhāsitaṃ:**The Buddha was referring to the cessation of the six sense fields when he said:*";
P_HTM[2692]="*‘tasmātiha, bhikkhave, se āyatane veditabbe, yattha cakkhu ca nirujjhati, rūpasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …**‘So you should understand that dimension where the eye ceases and perception of sights fades away. You should understand that dimension where the ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[2693]="*yattha mano ca nirujjhati, dhammasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe’ti.**mind ceases and perception of thoughts fades away.’*";
P_HTM[2694]="*Ayaṃ kho, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:**The Buddha gave this brief summary, then entered his dwelling without explaining the meaning in detail.*";
P_HTM[2695]="*‘tasmātiha, bhikkhave, se āyatane veditabbe yattha cakkhu ca nirujjhati, rūpasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2696]="*yattha mano ca nirujjhati, dhammasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2697]="*Imassa khvāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa evaṃ vitthārena atthaṃ ājānāmi.**And this is how I understand the detailed meaning of this summary.*";
P_HTM[2698]="*Ākaṅkhamānā ca pana tumhe āyasmanto bhagavantaṃyeva upasaṅkamatha;**If you wish, you may go to the Buddha and ask him about this.*";
P_HTM[2699]="*upasaṅkamitvā etamatthaṃ puccheyyātha.* **";
P_HTM[2700]="*Yathā vo bhagavā byākaroti tathā naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**You should remember it in line with the Buddha’s answer.”*";
P_HTM[2701]="*“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa paṭissutvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:**“Yes, reverend,” replied those mendicants. Then they rose from their seats and went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2702]="*“Yaṃ kho no, bhante, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[2703]="*‘tasmātiha, bhikkhave, se āyatane veditabbe yattha cakkhu ca nirujjhati, rūpasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2704]="*yattha jivhā ca nirujjhati, rasasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2705]="*yattha mano ca nirujjhati, dhammasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe’ti, tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ acirapakkantassa bhagavato etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2706]="*‘idaṃ kho no, āvuso, bhagavā saṅkhittena uddesaṃ uddisitvā vitthārena atthaṃ avibhajitvā uṭṭhāyāsanā vihāraṃ paviṭṭho:* **";
P_HTM[2707]="*“tasmātiha, bhikkhave, se āyatane veditabbe yattha cakkhu ca nirujjhati, rūpasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe … pe …* **";
P_HTM[2708]="*yattha mano ca nirujjhati, dhammasaññā ca nirujjhati, se āyatane veditabbe”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2709]="*Ko nu kho imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajeyyā’ti?* **";
P_HTM[2710]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ etadahosi:* **";
P_HTM[2711]="*‘ayaṃ kho āyasmā ānando satthu ceva saṃvaṇṇito, sambhāvito ca viññūnaṃ sabrahmacārīnaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2712]="*Pahoti cāyasmā ānando imassa bhagavatā saṅkhittena uddesassa uddiṭṭhassa vitthārena atthaṃ avibhattassa vitthārena atthaṃ vibhajituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2713]="*Yannūna mayaṃ yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkameyyāma; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyāmā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2714]="*Atha kho mayaṃ, bhante, yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkamimha; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etamatthaṃ paṭipucchimha.* **";
P_HTM[2715]="*Tesaṃ no, bhante, āyasmatā ānandena imehi ākārehi, imehi padehi, imehi byañjanehi attho vibhatto”ti.**Then they said, “And Ānanda explained the meaning to us in this manner, with these words and phrases.”*";
P_HTM[2716]="*“Paṇḍito, bhikkhave, ānando; mahāpañño, bhikkhave, ānando.**“Mendicants, Ānanda is astute, he has great wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2717]="*Mañcepi tumhe, bhikkhave, etamatthaṃ paṭipuccheyyātha, ahampi taṃ evamevaṃ byākareyyaṃ yathā taṃ ānandena byākataṃ.**If you came to me and asked this question, I would answer it in exactly the same way as Ānanda.*";
P_HTM[2718]="*Eso cevetassa attho. Evañca naṃ dhāreyyāthā”ti.**That is what it means, and that’s how you should remember it.”*";
P_HTM[2719]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2720]="*5. Sakkapañhasuttaṃ**The Question of Sakka*";
P_HTM[2721]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain.*";
P_HTM[2722]="*Atha kho sakko devānamindo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho sakko devānamindo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**And then Sakka, lord of gods, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2723]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life?*";
P_HTM[2724]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti?**What is the cause, what is the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life?”*";
P_HTM[2725]="*“Santi kho, devānaminda, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**“Lord of gods, there are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2726]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2727]="*Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti tadupādānaṃ.**their consciousness relies on that and grasps it.*";
P_HTM[2728]="*Saupādāno, devānaminda, bhikkhu no parinibbāyati … pe ….**A mendicant with grasping does not become extinguished.*";
P_HTM[2729]="*Santi kho, devānaminda, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …**There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …*";
P_HTM[2730]="*santi kho, devānaminda, manoviññeyyā dhammā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2731]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2732]="*Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti tadupādānaṃ.**their consciousness relies on that and grasps it.*";
P_HTM[2733]="*Saupādāno, devānaminda, bhikkhu no parinibbāyati.**A mendicant with grasping does not become extinguished.*";
P_HTM[2734]="*Ayaṃ kho, devānaminda, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti.**That’s the cause, that’s the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life.*";
P_HTM[2735]="*Santi ca kho, devānaminda, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2736]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2737]="*Tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato na tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti, na tadupādānaṃ.**their consciousness doesn’t rely on that and grasp it.*";
P_HTM[2738]="*Anupādāno, devānaminda, bhikkhu parinibbāyati … pe ….**A mendicant free of grasping becomes extinguished.*";
P_HTM[2739]="*Santi kho, devānaminda, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …**There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …*";
P_HTM[2740]="*santi kho, devānaminda, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2741]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2742]="*Tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato na tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti na tadupādānaṃ.**their consciousness doesn’t rely on that and grasp it.*";
P_HTM[2743]="*Anupādāno, devānaminda, bhikkhu parinibbāyati.**A mendicant free of grasping becomes extinguished.*";
P_HTM[2744]="*Ayaṃ kho, devānaminda, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti.**That’s the cause, that’s the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life.”*";
P_HTM[2745]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2746]="*6. Pañcasikhasuttaṃ**The Question of Pañcasikha*";
P_HTM[2747]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain.*";
P_HTM[2748]="*Atha kho pañcasikho gandhabbadevaputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho pañcasikho gandhabbadevaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**And then the fairy Pañcasikha went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2749]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life?*";
P_HTM[2750]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti?**What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life?”*";
P_HTM[2751]="*“Santi kho, pañcasikha, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā … pe …**“Pañcasikha, there are sights known by the eye …*";
P_HTM[2752]="*santi kho, pañcasikha, manoviññeyyā dhammā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2753]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati.**If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them,*";
P_HTM[2754]="*Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti tadupādānaṃ.**their consciousness relies on that and grasps it.*";
P_HTM[2755]="*Saupādāno, pañcasikha, bhikkhu no parinibbāyati.**A mendicant with grasping does not become extinguished.*";
P_HTM[2756]="*Ayaṃ kho, pañcasikha, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti.**That’s the cause, that’s the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life.*";
P_HTM[2757]="*Santi ca kho, pañcasikha, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā … pe …**There are sights known by the eye …*";
P_HTM[2758]="*santi kho, pañcasikha, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2759]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati, tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato na tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti, na tadupādānaṃ.**If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, their consciousness doesn’t rely on that and grasp it.*";
P_HTM[2760]="*Anupādāno, pañcasikha, bhikkhu parinibbāyati.**A mendicant free of grasping becomes extinguished.*";
P_HTM[2761]="*Ayaṃ kho, pañcasikha, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti.**That’s the cause, that’s the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life.”*";
P_HTM[2762]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2763]="*7. Sāriputtasaddhivihārikasuttaṃ**Sāriputta and the Pupil*";
P_HTM[2764]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā sāriputto sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time Venerable Sāriputta was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2765]="*Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then a certain mendicant went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[2766]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[2767]="*“saddhivihāriko, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhu sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvatto”ti.**“Reverend Sāriputta, a mendicant pupil of mine has rejected the training and returned to a lesser life.”*";
P_HTM[2768]="*“Evametaṃ, āvuso, hoti indriyesu aguttadvārassa, bhojane amattaññuno, jāgariyaṃ ananuyuttassa.**“That’s how it is, reverend, when someone doesn’t guard the sense doors, eats too much, and is not committed to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[2769]="*‘So vatāvuso, bhikkhu indriyesu aguttadvāro bhojane amattaññū jāgariyaṃ ananuyutto yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ santānessatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati.**It’s not possible for such a mendicant to maintain the full and pure spiritual life for the rest of their life.*";
P_HTM[2770]="*‘So vatāvuso, bhikkhu indriyesu guttadvāro, bhojane mattaññū, jāgariyaṃ anuyutto yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ santānessatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjati.**But it is possible for a mendicant to maintain the full and pure spiritual life for the rest of their life if they guard the sense doors, eat in moderation, and are committed to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[2771]="*Kathañcāvuso, indriyesu guttadvāro hoti?**And how does someone guard the sense doors?*";
P_HTM[2772]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When a mendicant sees a sight with the eyes, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[2773]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ, cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[2774]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[2775]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[2776]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[2777]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[2778]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī.**When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[2779]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati, rakkhati manindriyaṃ, manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving its restraint.*";
P_HTM[2780]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso, indriyesu guttadvāro hoti.**That’s how someone guards the sense doors.*";
P_HTM[2781]="*Kathañcāvuso, bhojane mattaññū hoti?**And how does someone eat in moderation?*";
P_HTM[2782]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso āhāraṃ āhāreti:**It’s when a mendicant reflects properly on the food that they eat:*";
P_HTM[2783]="*‘neva davāya, na madāya, na maṇḍanāya, na vibhūsanāya, yāvadeva imassa kāyassa ṭhitiyā yāpanāya, vihiṃsūparatiyā, brahmacariyānuggahāya. Iti purāṇañca vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me bhavissati, anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro cā’ti.**‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to sustain this body, to avoid harm, and to support spiritual practice. In this way, I shall put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and I will live blamelessly and at ease.’*";
P_HTM[2784]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso, bhojane mattaññū hoti.**That’s how someone eats in moderation.*";
P_HTM[2785]="*Kathañcāvuso, jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti?**And how is someone committed to wakefulness?*";
P_HTM[2786]="*Idhāvuso, bhikkhu divasaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ parisodheti.**It’s when a mendicant practices walking and sitting meditation by day, purifying their mind from obstacles.*";
P_HTM[2787]="*Rattiyā paṭhamaṃ yāmaṃ caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ parisodheti.**In the evening, they continue to practice walking and sitting meditation.*";
P_HTM[2788]="*Rattiyā majjhimaṃ yāmaṃ dakkhiṇena passena sīhaseyyaṃ kappeti pāde pādaṃ accādhāya sato sampajāno, uṭṭhānasaññaṃ manasi karitvā.**In the middle of the night, they lie down in the lion’s posture—on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other—mindful and aware, and focused on the time of getting up.*";
P_HTM[2789]="*Rattiyā pacchimaṃ yāmaṃ paccuṭṭhāya caṅkamena nisajjāya āvaraṇīyehi dhammehi cittaṃ parisodheti.**In the last part of the night, they get up and continue to practice walking and sitting meditation, purifying their mind from obstacles.*";
P_HTM[2790]="*Evaṃ kho, āvuso, jāgariyaṃ anuyutto hoti.**That’s how someone is committed to wakefulness.*";
P_HTM[2791]="*Tasmātihāvuso, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:**So you should train like this:*";
P_HTM[2792]="*‘indriyesu guttadvārā bhavissāma, bhojane mattaññuno, jāgariyaṃ anuyuttā’ti.**‘We will guard the sense doors, eat in moderation, and be committed to wakefulness.’*";
P_HTM[2793]="*Evañhi vo, āvuso, sikkhitabban”ti.**That’s how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[2794]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2795]="*8. Rāhulovādasuttaṃ**Advice to Rāhula*";
P_HTM[2796]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[2797]="*Atha kho bhagavato rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:**Then as he was in private retreat this thought came to his mind,*";
P_HTM[2798]="*“paripakkā kho rāhulassa vimuttiparipācaniyā dhammā;**“The qualities that ripen in freedom have ripened in Rāhula.*";
P_HTM[2799]="*yannūnāhaṃ rāhulaṃ uttariṃ āsavānaṃ khaye vineyyan”ti.**Why don’t I lead him further to the ending of defilements?”*";
P_HTM[2800]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā**Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, wandered for alms in Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[2801]="*pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ āmantesi:**After the meal, on his return from alms-round, he addressed Venerable Rāhula,*";
P_HTM[2802]="*“gaṇhāhi, rāhula, nisīdanaṃ.**“Rāhula, get your sitting cloth.*";
P_HTM[2803]="*Yena andhavanaṃ tenupasaṅkamissāma divāvihārāyā”ti.**Let’s go to the Dark Forest for the day’s meditation.”*";
P_HTM[2804]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā rāhulo bhagavato paṭissutvā nisīdanaṃ ādāya bhagavantaṃ piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhi.**“Yes, sir,” replied Rāhula. Taking his sitting cloth he followed behind the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2805]="*Tena kho pana samayena anekāni devatāsahassāni bhagavantaṃ anubandhāni honti:**Now at that time many thousands of deities followed the Buddha, thinking,*";
P_HTM[2806]="*“ajja bhagavā āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ uttariṃ āsavānaṃ khaye vinessatī”ti.**“Today the Buddha will lead Rāhula further to the ending of defilements!”*";
P_HTM[2807]="*Atha kho bhagavā andhavanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then the Buddha plunged deep into the Dark Forest and sat at the root of a tree on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[2808]="*Āyasmāpi kho rāhulo bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Rāhula bowed to the Buddha and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[2809]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:**The Buddha said to him:*";
P_HTM[2810]="*“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rāhula,**“What do you think, Rāhula?*";
P_HTM[2811]="*cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[2812]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2813]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[2814]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2815]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[2816]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[2817]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”. ()**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2818]="*“Rūpā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**“Are sights …*";
P_HTM[2819]="*“Aniccā, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2820]="*“Cakkhuviññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**eye consciousness …*";
P_HTM[2821]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2822]="*“Cakkhusamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**eye contact permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[2823]="*“Anicco, bhante” … pe ….**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[2824]="*“Yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedanāgataṃ, saññāgataṃ, saṅkhāragataṃ, viññāṇagataṃ, tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**“Anything included in feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness that arises conditioned by eye contact: is that permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[2825]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2826]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[2827]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2828]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[2829]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[2830]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante” … pe ….**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2831]="*“Jivhā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**“Is the ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[2832]="*“Aniccā, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2833]="*“Jivhāviññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2834]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2835]="*“Jivhāsamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2836]="*“Anicco, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2837]="*“Yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedanāgataṃ, saññāgataṃ, saṅkhāragataṃ, viññāṇagataṃ, tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2838]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[2839]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2840]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.* **";
P_HTM[2841]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:* **";
P_HTM[2842]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2843]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2844]="*“Mano nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**mind permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[2845]="*“Anicco, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2846]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[2847]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2848]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[2849]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[2850]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2851]="*“Dhammā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?**“Are thoughts …*";
P_HTM[2852]="*“Aniccā, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2853]="*“Manoviññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**mind consciousness …*";
P_HTM[2854]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe ….* **";
P_HTM[2855]="*“Manosamphasso nicco vā anicco vā”ti?**mind contact permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[2856]="*“Anicco, bhante” … pe ….**“Impermanent, sir.” …*";
P_HTM[2857]="*“Yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedanāgataṃ, saññāgataṃ, saṅkhāragataṃ, viññāṇagataṃ, tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?**“Anything included in feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness that arises conditioned by mind contact: is that permanent or impermanent?”*";
P_HTM[2858]="*“Aniccaṃ, bhante”.**“Impermanent, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2859]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?**“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”*";
P_HTM[2860]="*“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”.**“Suffering, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2861]="*“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:**“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to be regarded thus:*";
P_HTM[2862]="*‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?**‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”*";
P_HTM[2863]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.”*";
P_HTM[2864]="*“Evaṃ passaṃ, rāhula, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, rūpesupi nibbindati, cakkhuviññāṇepi nibbindati, cakkhusamphassepi nibbindati, yampidaṃ cakkhusamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ tasmimpi nibbindati … pe …**“Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and eye contact. And they become disillusioned with anything included in feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness that arises conditioned by eye contact.*";
P_HTM[2865]="*jivhāyapi nibbindati, rasesupi nibbindati, jivhāviññāṇepi nibbindati, jivhāsamphassepi nibbindati, yampidaṃ jivhāsamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ tasmimpi nibbindati … pe ….**They grow disillusioned with the ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[2866]="*Manasmimpi nibbindati, dhammesupi nibbindati, manoviññāṇepi nibbindati, manosamphassepi nibbindati, yampidaṃ manosamphassapaccayā uppajjati vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ tasmimpi nibbindati.**They grow disillusioned with the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and mind contact. And they grow disillusioned with anything included in feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness that arises conditioned by mind contact.*";
P_HTM[2867]="*Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[2868]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[2869]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2870]="*Attamano āyasmā rāhulo bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandi.**Satisfied, Venerable Rāhula was happy with what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[2871]="*Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne āyasmato rāhulassa anupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimucci.**And while this discourse was being spoken, Rāhula’s mind was freed from defilements by not grasping.*";
P_HTM[2872]="*Anekānañca devatāsahassānaṃ virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi:**And the stainless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in those thousands of deities:*";
P_HTM[2873]="*“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti.**“Everything that has a beginning has an end.”*";
P_HTM[2874]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2875]="*9. Saṃyojaniyadhammasuttaṃ**Things Prone to Being Fettered*";
P_HTM[2876]="*“Saṃyojaniye ca, bhikkhave, dhamme desessāmi saṃyojanañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the things that are prone to being fettered, and the fetter.*";
P_HTM[2877]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[2878]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyā dhammā, katamañca saṃyojanaṃ?**What are the things that are prone to being fettered? And what is the fetter?*";
P_HTM[2879]="*Santi, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2880]="*Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyā dhammā.**These are called the things that are prone to being fettered.*";
P_HTM[2881]="*Yo tattha chandarāgo, taṃ tattha saṃyojanaṃ … pe …**The desire and greed for them is the fetter.*";
P_HTM[2882]="*santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …**There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …*";
P_HTM[2883]="*santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2884]="*Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyā dhammā.**These are called the things that are prone to being fettered.*";
P_HTM[2885]="*Yo tattha chandarāgo taṃ tattha saṃyojanan”ti.**The desire and greed for them is the fetter.”*";
P_HTM[2886]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2887]="*10. Upādāniyadhammasuttaṃ**Things Prone to Being Grasped*";
P_HTM[2888]="*“Upādāniye ca, bhikkhave, dhamme desessāmi upādānañca.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the things that are prone to being grasped, and the grasping.*";
P_HTM[2889]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[2890]="*Katame ca, bhikkhave, upādāniyā dhammā, katamañca upādānaṃ?**What are the things that are prone to being grasped? And what is the grasping?*";
P_HTM[2891]="*Santi, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2892]="*Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, upādāniyā dhammā.**These are called the things that are prone to being grasped.*";
P_HTM[2893]="*Yo tattha chandarāgo, taṃ tattha upādānaṃ … pe …**The desire and greed for them is the grasping.*";
P_HTM[2894]="*santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …**There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …*";
P_HTM[2895]="*santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2896]="*Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, upādāniyā dhammā.**These are called the things that are prone to being grasped.*";
P_HTM[2897]="*Yo tattha chandarāgo taṃ tattha upādānan”ti.**The desire and greed for them is the grasping.”*";
P_HTM[2898]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2899]="*Lokakāmaguṇavaggo dutiyo.* **";
P_HTM[2900]="*Mārapāsena dve vuttā,* **";
P_HTM[2901]="*lokakāmaguṇena ca;* **";
P_HTM[2902]="*Sakko pañcasikho ceva,* **";
P_HTM[2903]="*sāriputto ca rāhulo;* **";
P_HTM[2904]="*Saṃyojanaṃ upādānaṃ,* **";
P_HTM[2905]="*vaggo tena pavuccatīti.* **";
P_HTM[2906]="*13. Gahapativaggo**Householders*";
P_HTM[2907]="*1. Vesālīsuttaṃ**At Vesālī*";
P_HTM[2908]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof.*";
P_HTM[2909]="*Atha kho uggo gahapati vesāliko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho uggo gahapati vesāliko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the householder Ugga of Vesālī went up to the Buddha, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2910]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life?*";
P_HTM[2911]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti?**What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life?”*";
P_HTM[2912]="*“Santi kho, gahapati, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**“Householder, there are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2913]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati. Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti tadupādānaṃ.**If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them, their consciousness relies on that and grasps it.*";
P_HTM[2914]="*Saupādāno, gahapati, bhikkhu no parinibbāyati … pe …**A mendicant with grasping does not become extinguished.*";
P_HTM[2915]="*santi kho, gahapati, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …**There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …*";
P_HTM[2916]="*santi kho, gahapati, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2917]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati. Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti tadupādānaṃ.**If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them, their consciousness relies on that and grasps it.*";
P_HTM[2918]="*Saupādāno, gahapati, bhikkhu no parinibbāyati.**A mendicant with grasping does not become extinguished.*";
P_HTM[2919]="*Ayaṃ kho, gahapati, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti.**That’s the cause, that’s the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life.*";
P_HTM[2920]="*Santi ca kho, gahapati, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā, iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2921]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati. Tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato na tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti, na tadupādānaṃ.**If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, their consciousness doesn’t rely on that and grasp it.*";
P_HTM[2922]="*Anupādāno, gahapati, bhikkhu parinibbāyati … pe …**A mendicant free of grasping becomes extinguished.*";
P_HTM[2923]="*santi kho, gahapati, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …**There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …*";
P_HTM[2924]="*santi kho, gahapati, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing.*";
P_HTM[2925]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati, tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato. Na tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti, na tadupādānaṃ.**If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, their consciousness doesn’t rely on that and grasp it.*";
P_HTM[2926]="*Anupādāno, gahapati, bhikkhu parinibbāyati.**A mendicant free of grasping becomes extinguished.*";
P_HTM[2927]="*Ayaṃ kho, gahapati, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti.**That’s the cause, that’s the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life.”*";
P_HTM[2928]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2929]="*2. Vajjīsuttaṃ**In the Land of the Vajjis*";
P_HTM[2930]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vajjīsu viharati hatthigāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Vajjis at the village of Hatthi.*";
P_HTM[2931]="*Atha kho uggo gahapati hatthigāmako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho uggo gahapati hatthigāmako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the householder Ugga of Hatthi went up to the Buddha, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2932]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life?*";
P_HTM[2933]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti?**What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life?” …*";
P_HTM[2934]="*(Yathā purimasuttantaṃ, evaṃ vitthāretabbaṃ.)**(This should be told in full as in the previous discourse.)*";
P_HTM[2935]="*“Ayaṃ kho, gahapati, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2936]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2937]="*3. Nāḷandasuttaṃ**At Nālandā*";
P_HTM[2938]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā nāḷandāyaṃ viharati pāvārikambavane.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Nālandā in Pāvārika’s mango grove.*";
P_HTM[2939]="*Atha kho, upāli gahapati, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho, upāli gahapati, bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the householder Upāli went up to the Buddha … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[2940]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life?*";
P_HTM[2941]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti?**What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life?” …*";
P_HTM[2942]="*(Yathā purimasuttantaṃ, evaṃ vitthāretabbaṃ.)**(This should be told in full as in SN 35.124.)*";
P_HTM[2943]="*“Ayaṃ kho, gahapati, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[2944]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2945]="*4. Bhāradvājasuttaṃ**With Bhāradvāja*";
P_HTM[2946]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā piṇḍolabhāradvājo kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time Venerable Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2947]="*Atha kho rājā udeno yenāyasmā piṇḍolabhāradvājo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā piṇḍolabhāradvājena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then King Udena went up to Piṇḍola Bhāradvāja and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[2948]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā udeno āyasmantaṃ piṇḍolabhāradvājaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2949]="*“ko nu kho, bho bhāradvāja, hetu ko paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā anikīḷitāvino kāmesu yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caranti, addhānañca āpādentī”ti?**“Master Bhāradvāja, there are these young monks who are youthful, black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life; and they’ve never played around with sensual pleasures. What is the cause, what is the reason why they practice the full and pure spiritual life as long as they live, maintaining it for a long time?”*";
P_HTM[2950]="*“Vuttaṃ kho etaṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena:**“Great king, this has been stated by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha:*";
P_HTM[2951]="*‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, mātumattīsu mātucittaṃ upaṭṭhapetha, bhaginimattīsu bhaginicittaṃ upaṭṭhapetha, dhītumattīsu dhītucittaṃ upaṭṭhapethā’ti.**‘Please, monks, think of women your mother’s age as your mother. Think of women your sister’s age as your sister. And think of women your daughter’s age as your daughter.’*";
P_HTM[2952]="*Ayaṃ kho, mahārāja, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā anikīḷitāvino kāmesu yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caranti, addhānañca āpādentī”ti.**This is a cause, great king, this is a reason why these young monks practice the full and pure spiritual life as long as they live, maintaining it for a long time.”*";
P_HTM[2953]="*“Lolaṃ kho, bho bhāradvāja, cittaṃ.**“But Master Bhāradvāja, the mind is wanton.*";
P_HTM[2954]="*Appekadā mātumattīsupi lobhadhammā uppajjanti, bhaginimattīsupi lobhadhammā uppajjanti, dhītumattīsupi lobhadhammā uppajjanti.**Sometimes thoughts of desire come up even for women your mother’s age, your sister’s age, or your daughter’s age.*";
P_HTM[2955]="*Atthi nu kho, bho bhāradvāja, añño ca hetu, añño ca paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā … pe … addhānañca āpādentī”ti?**Is there another cause, another reason why these young monks live the full and pure spiritual life for their entire life?”*";
P_HTM[2956]="*“Vuttaṃ kho etaṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena:**“Great king, this has been stated by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha:*";
P_HTM[2957]="*‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, imameva kāyaṃ uddhaṃ pādatalā adho kesamatthakā tacapariyantaṃ pūraṃ nānappakārassa asucino paccavekkhatha—**‘Please, monks, examine your own body up from the soles of the feet and down from the tips of the hairs, wrapped in skin and full of many kinds of filth.*";
P_HTM[2958]="*atthi imasmiṃ kāye kesā lomā nakhā dantā taco maṃsaṃ nhāru aṭṭhi aṭṭhimiñjaṃ vakkaṃ hadayaṃ yakanaṃ kilomakaṃ pihakaṃ papphāsaṃ antaṃ antaguṇaṃ udariyaṃ karīsaṃ pittaṃ semhaṃ pubbo lohitaṃ sedo medo assu vasā kheḷo siṅghāṇikā lasikā muttan’ti.**In this body there is head hair, body hair, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, sinews, bones, bone marrow, kidneys, heart, liver, diaphragm, spleen, lungs, intestines, mesentery, undigested food, feces, bile, phlegm, pus, blood, sweat, fat, tears, grease, saliva, snot, synovial fluid, urine.’*";
P_HTM[2959]="*Ayampi kho, mahārāja, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā … pe … addhānañca āpādentī”ti.**This is also a cause, great king, this is a reason why these young monks live the full and pure spiritual life for their entire life, maintaining it for a long time.”*";
P_HTM[2960]="*“Ye te, bho bhāradvāja, bhikkhū bhāvitakāyā bhāvitasīlā bhāvitacittā bhāvitapaññā, tesaṃ taṃ sukaraṃ hoti.**“This is easy to do for those mendicants who have developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2961]="*Ye ca kho te, bho bhāradvāja, bhikkhū abhāvitakāyā abhāvitasīlā abhāvitacittā abhāvitapaññā, tesaṃ taṃ dukkaraṃ hoti.**But it’s hard to do for those mendicants who have not developed their physical endurance, ethics, mind, and wisdom.*";
P_HTM[2962]="*Appekadā, bho bhāradvāja, asubhato manasi karissāmīti subhatova āgacchati.**Sometimes I plan to focus on something as ugly, but only its beauty comes to mind.*";
P_HTM[2963]="*Atthi nu kho, bho bhāradvāja, añño ca kho hetu añño ca paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā … pe … addhānañca āpādentī”ti?**Is there another cause, another reason why these young monks live the full and pure spiritual life for their entire life?”*";
P_HTM[2964]="*“Vuttaṃ kho etaṃ, mahārāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena:**“Great king, this has been stated by the Blessed One, who knows and sees, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha:*";
P_HTM[2965]="*‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, indriyesu guttadvārā viharatha.**‘Please, monks, live with sense doors guarded.*";
P_HTM[2966]="*Cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā mā nimittaggāhino ahuvattha, mānubyañjanaggāhino.**When you see a sight with your eyes, don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[2967]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjatha. Rakkhatha cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjatha.**If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, practice restraint, protect the faculty of sight, and achieve its restraint.*";
P_HTM[2968]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**When you hear a sound with your ears …*";
P_HTM[2969]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When you smell an odor with your nose …*";
P_HTM[2970]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When you taste a flavor with your tongue …*";
P_HTM[2971]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When you feel a touch with your body …*";
P_HTM[2972]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya mā nimittaggāhino ahuvattha, mānubyañjanaggāhino.**When you know a thought with your mind, don’t get caught up in the features and details.*";
P_HTM[2973]="*Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjatha. Rakkhatha manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjathā’ti.**If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, practice restraint, protect the faculty of mind, and achieve its restraint.’*";
P_HTM[2974]="*Ayampi kho, mahārāja, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā anikīḷitāvino kāmesu yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caranti, addhānañca āpādentī”ti.**This is also a cause, great king, this is a reason why these young monks practice the full and pure spiritual life as long as they live, maintaining it for a long time.”*";
P_HTM[2975]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho bhāradvāja; abbhutaṃ, bho bhāradvāja.**“It’s incredible, Master Bhāradvāja, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[2976]="*Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ, bho bhāradvāja, tena bhagavatā jānatā passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena.**How well this was said by the Buddha!*";
P_HTM[2977]="*Esova kho, bho bhāradvāja, hetu, esa paccayo yenime daharā bhikkhū susū kāḷakesā bhadrena yobbanena samannāgatā paṭhamena vayasā anikīḷitāvino kāmesu yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caranti, addhānañca āpādentīti.**This is the real cause, this is the reason why these young monks practice the full and pure spiritual life as long as they live, maintaining it for a long time.*";
P_HTM[2978]="*Ahampi kho, bho bhāradvāja, yasmiṃ samaye arakkhiteneva kāyena, arakkhitāya vācāya, arakkhitena cittena, anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā, asaṃvutehi indriyehi antepuraṃ pavisāmi, ativiya maṃ tasmiṃ samaye lobhadhammā parisahanti.**For sometimes I too enter the harem with unprotected body, speech, mind, mindfulness, and sense faculties. At those times powerful thoughts of desire get the better of me.*";
P_HTM[2979]="*Yasmiñca khvāhaṃ, bho bhāradvāja, samaye rakkhiteneva kāyena, rakkhitāya vācāya, rakkhitena cittena, upaṭṭhitāya satiyā, saṃvutehi indriyehi antepuraṃ pavisāmi, na maṃ tathā tasmiṃ samaye lobhadhammā parisahanti.**But sometimes I enter the harem with protected body, speech, mind, mindfulness, and sense faculties. At those times such thoughts of desire don’t get the better of me.*";
P_HTM[2980]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bho bhāradvāja, abhikkantaṃ, bho bhāradvāja.**Excellent, Master Bhāradvāja! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[2981]="*Seyyathāpi, bho bhāradvāja, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā bhāradvājena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Bhāradvāja has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[2982]="*Esāhaṃ, bho bhāradvāja, taṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca, bhikkhusaṃghañca.**I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[2983]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ bhāradvājo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Master Bhāradvāja remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[2984]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2985]="*5. Soṇasuttaṃ**With Soṇa*";
P_HTM[2986]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground.*";
P_HTM[2987]="*Atha kho soṇo gahapatiputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho soṇo gahapatiputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the householder Soṇa went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2988]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life?*";
P_HTM[2989]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti?**What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life?” …*";
P_HTM[2990]="*(Yathā purimasuttantaṃ, evaṃ vitthāretabbaṃ.)**(This should be told in full as in SN 35.118.)*";
P_HTM[2991]="*Ayaṃ kho, soṇa, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantīti.* **";
P_HTM[2992]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2993]="*6. Ghositasuttaṃ**With Ghosita*";
P_HTM[2994]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2995]="*Atha kho ghosito gahapati yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho ghosito gahapati āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:**Then the householder Ghosita went up to Venerable Ānanda, and said to him:*";
P_HTM[2996]="*“‘dhātunānattaṃ, dhātunānattan’ti, bhante ānanda, vuccati.**“Sir, Ānanda, they speak of ‘the diversity of elements’.*";
P_HTM[2997]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, dhātunānattaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā”ti?**In what way did the Buddha speak of the diversity of elements?”*";
P_HTM[2998]="*“Saṃvijjati kho, gahapati, cakkhudhātu, rūpā ca manāpā, cakkhuviññāṇañca sukhavedaniyaṃ.**“Householder, the eye element is found, as are agreeable sights, and eye consciousness.*";
P_HTM[2999]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhā vedanā.**Pleasant feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as pleasant.*";
P_HTM[3000]="*Saṃvijjati kho, gahapati, cakkhudhātu, rūpā ca amanāpā, cakkhuviññāṇañca dukkhavedaniyaṃ.**The eye element is found, as are disagreeable sights, and eye consciousness.*";
P_HTM[3001]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhā vedanā.**Painful feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as painful.*";
P_HTM[3002]="*Saṃvijjati kho, gahapati, cakkhudhātu, rūpā ca manāpā upekkhāvedaniyā, cakkhuviññāṇañca adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ.**The eye element is found, as are sights that are a basis for equanimity, and eye consciousness.*";
P_HTM[3003]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā … pe …**Neutral feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as neutral.*";
P_HTM[3004]="*saṃvijjati kho, gahapati, jivhādhātu, rasā ca manāpā, jivhāviññāṇañca sukhavedaniyaṃ.**The ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[3005]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhā vedanā.* **";
P_HTM[3006]="*Saṃvijjati kho, gahapati, jivhādhātu, rasā ca amanāpā, jivhāviññāṇañca dukkhavedaniyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3007]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhā vedanā.* **";
P_HTM[3008]="*Saṃvijjati kho, gahapati, jivhādhātu, rasā ca upekkhāvedaniyā, jivhāviññāṇañca adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3009]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3010]="*saṃvijjati kho, gahapati, manodhātu, dhammā ca manāpā, manoviññāṇañca sukhavedaniyaṃ.**mind element is found, as are agreeable thoughts, and mind consciousness.*";
P_HTM[3011]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhā vedanā.**Pleasant feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as pleasant.*";
P_HTM[3012]="*Saṃvijjati kho, gahapati, manodhātu, dhammā ca amanāpā, manoviññāṇañca dukkhavedaniyaṃ.**The mind element is found, as are disagreeable thoughts, and mind consciousness.*";
P_HTM[3013]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhā vedanā.**Painful feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as painful.*";
P_HTM[3014]="*Saṃvijjati kho, gahapati, manodhātu, dhammā ca upekkhāvedaniyā, manoviññāṇañca adukkhamasukhavedaniyaṃ.**The mind element is found, as are thoughts that are a basis for equanimity, and mind consciousness.*";
P_HTM[3015]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā.**Neutral feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as neutral.*";
P_HTM[3016]="*Ettāvatā kho, gahapati, dhātunānattaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā”ti.**This is how the Buddha spoke of the diversity of elements.”*";
P_HTM[3017]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3018]="*7. Hāliddikānisuttaṃ**With Hāliddikāni*";
P_HTM[3019]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahākaccāno avantīsu viharati kuraraghare papāte pabbate.**At one time Venerable Mahākaccāna was staying in the land of the Avantis near Kuraraghara on Steep Mountain.*";
P_HTM[3020]="*Atha kho hāliddikāni gahapati yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho hāliddikāni gahapati āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etadavoca:**Then the householder Hāliddikāni went up to Venerable Mahākaccāna … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[3021]="*“vuttamidaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā:**“Sir, this was said by the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[3022]="*‘dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ; phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattan’ti.**‘Diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings.’*";
P_HTM[3023]="*Kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ; phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattan”ti?**How does diversity of elements give rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings?”*";
P_HTM[3024]="*“Idha, gahapati, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā ‘manāpaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti cakkhuviññāṇaṃ sukhavedaniyañca.**“Householder, it’s when a mendicant sees a sight and understands it to be agreeable.*";
P_HTM[3025]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhā vedanā.**There is eye consciousness; and pleasant feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as pleasant.*";
P_HTM[3026]="*Cakkhunā kho paneva rūpaṃ disvā ‘amanāpaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti cakkhuviññāṇaṃ dukkhavedaniyañca.**Then they see a sight and understand it to be disagreeable.*";
P_HTM[3027]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhā vedanā.**There is eye consciousness; and painful feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as painful.*";
P_HTM[3028]="*Cakkhunā kho paneva rūpaṃ disvā ‘upekkhāṭṭhāniyaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti cakkhuviññāṇaṃ adukkhamasukhavedaniyañca.**Then they see a sight and understand it to be a basis for equanimity.*";
P_HTM[3029]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā.**There is eye consciousness; and neutral feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as neutral.*";
P_HTM[3030]="*Puna caparaṃ, gahapati, bhikkhu sotena saddaṃ sutvā … pe …**Furthermore, a mendicant hears a sound with the ear …*";
P_HTM[3031]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … pe …**smells an odor with the nose …*";
P_HTM[3032]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … pe …**tastes a flavor with the tongue …*";
P_HTM[3033]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … pe …**feels a touch with the body …*";
P_HTM[3034]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya ‘manāpaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti manoviññāṇaṃ sukhavedaniyañca.**knows a thought with the mind and understands it to be agreeable.*";
P_HTM[3035]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhā vedanā.**There is mind consciousness; and pleasant feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as pleasant.*";
P_HTM[3036]="*Manasā kho paneva dhammaṃ viññāya ‘amanāpaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti manoviññāṇaṃ dukkhavedaniyañca.**Then they know a thought and understand it to be disagreeable.*";
P_HTM[3037]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati dukkhā vedanā.**There is mind consciousness; and painful feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as painful.*";
P_HTM[3038]="*Manasā kho paneva dhammaṃ viññāya ‘upekkhāṭṭhāniyaṃ itthetan’ti pajānāti manoviññāṇaṃ adukkhamasukhavedaniyañca.**Then they know a thought and understand it to be a basis for equanimity.*";
P_HTM[3039]="*Phassaṃ paṭicca uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā.**Neutral feeling arises dependent on a contact to be experienced as neutral.*";
P_HTM[3040]="*Evaṃ kho, gahapati, dhātunānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati phassanānattaṃ; phassanānattaṃ paṭicca uppajjati vedanānānattan”ti.**That’s how diversity of elements gives rise to diversity of contacts, and diversity of contacts gives rise to diversity of feelings.”*";
P_HTM[3041]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3042]="*8. Nakulapitusuttaṃ**Nakula’s Father*";
P_HTM[3043]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood.*";
P_HTM[3044]="*Atha kho nakulapitā gahapati yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho nakulapitā gahapati bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:**Then the householder Nakula’s father went up to the Buddha … and asked him,*";
P_HTM[3045]="*“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti?**“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings aren’t fully extinguished in the present life?*";
P_HTM[3046]="*Ko pana, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti?**What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why some sentient beings are fully extinguished in the present life?” …*";
P_HTM[3047]="*“Santi kho, gahapati, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.**(This should be told in full as in SN 35.118.)*";
P_HTM[3048]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati.* **";
P_HTM[3049]="*Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti tadupādānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3050]="*Saupādāno, gahapati, bhikkhu no parinibbāyati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3051]="*santi kho, gahapati, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3052]="*santi kho, gahapati, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.* **";
P_HTM[3053]="*Tañce bhikkhu abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati.* **";
P_HTM[3054]="*Tassa taṃ abhinandato abhivadato ajjhosāya tiṭṭhato tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti tadupādānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3055]="*Saupādāno, gahapati, bhikkhu no parinibbāyati.* **";
P_HTM[3056]="*Ayaṃ kho, gahapati, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme no parinibbāyanti.* **";
P_HTM[3057]="*Santi ca kho, gahapati, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.* **";
P_HTM[3058]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati.* **";
P_HTM[3059]="*Tassa taṃ anabhinandato anabhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato na tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti, na tadupādānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3060]="*Anupādāno, gahapati, bhikkhu parinibbāyati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3061]="*santi kho, gahapati, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3062]="*santi kho, gahapati, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā.* **";
P_HTM[3063]="*Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati.* **";
P_HTM[3064]="*Tassa taṃ nābhinandato nābhivadato anajjhosāya tiṭṭhato na tannissitaṃ viññāṇaṃ hoti na tadupādānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3065]="*Anupādāno, gahapati, bhikkhu parinibbāyati.* **";
P_HTM[3066]="*Ayaṃ kho, gahapati, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo yena m’idhekacce sattā diṭṭheva dhamme parinibbāyantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3067]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3068]="*9. Lohiccasuttaṃ**With Lohicca*";
P_HTM[3069]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā mahākaccāno avantīsu viharati makkarakate araññakuṭikāyaṃ.**At one time Venerable Mahākaccāna was staying in the land of the Avantis in a wilderness hut near Makkarakaṭa.*";
P_HTM[3070]="*Atha kho lohiccassa brāhmaṇassa sambahulā antevāsikā kaṭṭhahārakā māṇavakā yenāyasmato mahākaccānassa araññakuṭikā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā parito parito kuṭikāya anucaṅkamanti anuvicaranti uccāsaddā mahāsaddā kānici kānici seleyyakāni karonti:**Then several youths, students of the brahmin Lohicca, approached Mahākaccāna’s wilderness hut while collecting firewood. They walked and wandered all around the hut, making a dreadful racket and all kinds of jeers:*";
P_HTM[3071]="*“ime pana muṇḍakā samaṇakā ibbhā kaṇhā bandhupādāpaccā, imesaṃ bharatakānaṃ sakkatā garukatā mānitā pūjitā apacitā”ti.**“These shavelings, fake ascetics, riffraff, black spawn from the feet of our Kinsman, the Lord! They’re honored, respected, esteemed, revered, and venerated by those who pretend to inherit Vedic culture.”*";
P_HTM[3072]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākaccāno vihārā nikkhamitvā te māṇavake etadavoca:**And then Mahākaccāna left his dwelling and said to those brahmin students,*";
P_HTM[3073]="*“mā māṇavakā saddamakattha;**“Students, stop being so noisy.*";
P_HTM[3074]="*dhammaṃ vo bhāsissāmī”ti.**I will speak to you on the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3075]="*Evaṃ vutte, te māṇavakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ.**When this was said, the students fell silent.*";
P_HTM[3076]="*Atha kho āyasmā mahākaccāno te māṇavake gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:**Then Mahākaccāna recited these verses for them.*";
P_HTM[3077]="*“Sīluttamā pubbatarā ahesuṃ,**“The brahmins of old excelled in ethics,*";
P_HTM[3078]="*Te brāhmaṇā ye purāṇaṃ saranti;**and remembered the ancient traditions.*";
P_HTM[3079]="*Guttāni dvārāni surakkhitāni,**Their sense doors were guarded, well protected,*";
P_HTM[3080]="*Ahesuṃ tesaṃ abhibhuyya kodhaṃ.**and they had mastered anger.*";
P_HTM[3081]="*Dhamme ca jhāne ca ratā ahesuṃ,**Those brahmins who remembered the ancient traditions*";
P_HTM[3082]="*Te brāhmaṇā ye purāṇaṃ saranti.**enjoyed virtue and absorption.*";
P_HTM[3083]="*Ime ca vokkamma japāmaseti,**But these have lost their way. Claiming to recite,*";
P_HTM[3084]="*Gottena mattā visamaṃ caranti;**they live out of balance, judging everyone by their clan.*";
P_HTM[3085]="*Kodhābhibhūtā puthuattadaṇḍā,**Mastered by anger, they take up many arms,*";
P_HTM[3086]="*Virajjamānā sataṇhātaṇhesu.**attacking both the strong and the weak.*";
P_HTM[3087]="*Aguttadvārassa bhavanti moghā,**All is vain for someone who doesn’t guard the sense doors,*";
P_HTM[3088]="*Supineva laddhaṃ purisassa vittaṃ;**like the wealth a person finds in a dream.*";
P_HTM[3089]="*Anāsakā thaṇḍilasāyikā ca,**Fasting, sleeping on bare ground,*";
P_HTM[3090]="*Pāto sinānañca tayo ca vedā.**bathing at dawn, the three Vedas,*";
P_HTM[3091]="*Kharājinaṃ jaṭāpaṅko,**rough hides, dreadlocks, and dirt,*";
P_HTM[3092]="*mantā sīlabbataṃ tapo;**hymns, precepts and observances, and self-mortification,*";
P_HTM[3093]="*Kuhanā vaṅkadaṇḍā ca,**those fake bent staffs,*";
P_HTM[3094]="*udakācamanāni ca;**and rinsing with water.*";
P_HTM[3095]="*Vaṇṇā ete brāhmaṇānaṃ,**These emblems of the brahmins*";
P_HTM[3096]="*katā kiñcikkhabhāvanā.**are only used to generate profits.*";
P_HTM[3097]="*Cittañca susamāhitaṃ,**A mind that’s serene,*";
P_HTM[3098]="*vippasannamanāvilaṃ;**clear and undisturbed,*";
P_HTM[3099]="*Akhilaṃ sabbabhūtesu,**kind to all creatures:*";
P_HTM[3100]="*so maggo brahmapattiyā”ti.**that’s the path to attainment of Brahmā!”*";
P_HTM[3101]="*Atha kho te māṇavakā kupitā anattamanā yena lohicco brāhmaṇo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā lohiccaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavocuṃ:**Then those students, offended and upset, went to the brahmin Lohicca and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3102]="*“yagghe bhavaṃ jāneyya, samaṇo mahākaccāno brāhmaṇānaṃ mante ekaṃsena apavadati, paṭikkosatī”ti?**“Please, master, you should know this. The ascetic Mahākaccāna condemns and rejects outright the hymns of the brahmins!”*";
P_HTM[3103]="*Evaṃ vutte, lohicco brāhmaṇo kupito ahosi anattamano.**When they said this, Lohicca was offended and upset.*";
P_HTM[3104]="*Atha kho lohiccassa brāhmaṇassa etadahosi:**Then he thought,*";
P_HTM[3105]="*“na kho pana metaṃ patirūpaṃ yohaṃ aññadatthu māṇavakānaṃyeva sutvā samaṇaṃ mahākaccānaṃ akkoseyyaṃ paribhāseyyaṃ.**“But it wouldn’t be appropriate for me to abuse or insult the ascetic Mahākaccāna solely because of what I’ve heard from these students.*";
P_HTM[3106]="*Yannūnāhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā puccheyyan”ti.**Why don’t I go and ask him about it?”*";
P_HTM[3107]="*Atha kho lohicco brāhmaṇo tehi māṇavakehi saddhiṃ yenāyasmā mahākaccāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā mahākaccānena saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then the brahmin Lohicca together with those students went to Venerable Mahākaccāna and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[3108]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho lohicco brāhmaṇo āyasmantaṃ mahākaccānaṃ etadavoca:**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3109]="*“āgamaṃsu nu khvidha, bho kaccāna, amhākaṃ sambahulā antevāsikā kaṭṭhahārakā māṇavakā”ti?**“Master Kaccāna, did several young students of mine come by here collecting firewood?”*";
P_HTM[3110]="*“Āgamaṃsu khvidha te, brāhmaṇa, sambahulā antevāsikā kaṭṭhahārakā māṇavakā”ti.**“They did, brahmin.”*";
P_HTM[3111]="*“Ahu pana bhoto kaccānassa tehi māṇavakehi saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti?**“But did you have some discussion with them?”*";
P_HTM[3112]="*“Ahu kho me, brāhmaṇa, tehi māṇavakehi saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti.**“I did.”*";
P_HTM[3113]="*“Yathā kathaṃ pana bhoto kaccānassa tehi māṇavakehi saddhiṃ ahosi kathāsallāpo”ti?**“But what kind of discussion did you have with them?”*";
P_HTM[3114]="*“Evaṃ kho me, brāhmaṇa, tehi māṇavakehi saddhiṃ ahosi kathāsallāpo:**“This is the discussion I had with these students.”*";
P_HTM[3115]="*‘Sīluttamā pubbatarā ahesuṃ,**(Mahākaccāna repeats the verses.)*";
P_HTM[3116]="*Te brāhmaṇā ye purāṇaṃ saranti;* **";
P_HTM[3117]="*… pe …* **";
P_HTM[3118]="*Akhilaṃ sabbabhūtesu,* **";
P_HTM[3119]="*So maggo brahmapattiyā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3120]="*Evaṃ kho me, brāhmaṇa, tehi māṇavakehi saddhiṃ ahosi kathāsallāpo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3121]="*“‘Aguttadvāro’ti bhavaṃ kaccāno āha.**“Master Kaccāna spoke of someone who doesn’t guard the sense doors.*";
P_HTM[3122]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bho kaccāna, aguttadvāro hotī”ti?**How do you define someone who doesn’t guard the sense doors?”*";
P_HTM[3123]="*“Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe adhimuccati, appiyarūpe rūpe byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati, parittacetaso**“Brahmin, take someone who sees a sight with their eyes. If it’s pleasant they hold on to it, but if it’s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body unestablished and their heart restricted.*";
P_HTM[3124]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[3125]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[3126]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[3127]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[3128]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[3129]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme adhimuccati, appiyarūpe ca dhamme byāpajjati, anupaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati, parittacetaso**When they know a thought with their mind, if it’s pleasant they hold on to it, but if it’s unpleasant they dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body unestablished and a limited heart.*";
P_HTM[3130]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[3131]="*Evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, aguttadvāro hotī”ti.**That’s how someone doesn’t guard the sense doors.”*";
P_HTM[3132]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho kaccāna, abbhutaṃ, bho kaccāna.**“It’s incredible, Master Kaccāna, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[3133]="*Yāvañcidaṃ bhotā kaccānena aguttadvārova samāno aguttadvāroti akkhāto.**How accurately you’ve explained someone whose sense doors are unguarded!*";
P_HTM[3134]="*‘Guttadvāro’ti bhavaṃ kaccāno āha.**You also spoke of someone who does guard the sense doors.*";
P_HTM[3135]="*Kittāvatā nu kho, bho kaccāna, guttadvāro hotī”ti?**How do you define someone who does guard the sense doors?”*";
P_HTM[3136]="*“Idha, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā piyarūpe rūpe nādhimuccati, appiyarūpe rūpe na byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati, appamāṇacetaso**“Brahmin, take someone who sees a sight with their eyes. If it’s pleasant they don’t hold on to it, and if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body established and a limitless heart.*";
P_HTM[3137]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[3138]="*Sotena saddaṃ sutvā …**When they hear a sound with their ears …*";
P_HTM[3139]="*ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā …**When they smell an odor with their nose …*";
P_HTM[3140]="*jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā …**When they taste a flavor with their tongue …*";
P_HTM[3141]="*kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā …**When they feel a touch with their body …*";
P_HTM[3142]="*manasā dhammaṃ viññāya piyarūpe dhamme nādhimuccati, appiyarūpe dhamme na byāpajjati, upaṭṭhitakāyassati ca viharati, appamāṇacetaso**When they know a thought with their mind, if it’s pleasant they don’t hold on to it, and if it’s unpleasant they don’t dislike it. They live with mindfulness of the body established and a limitless heart.*";
P_HTM[3143]="*tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, yatthassa te uppannā pāpakā akusalā dhammā aparisesā nirujjhanti.**And they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where those arisen bad, unskillful qualities cease without anything left over.*";
P_HTM[3144]="*Evaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, guttadvāro hotī”ti.**That’s how someone guards the sense doors.”*";
P_HTM[3145]="*“Acchariyaṃ, bho kaccāna, abbhutaṃ, bho kaccāna.**“It’s incredible, Master Kaccāna, it’s amazing!*";
P_HTM[3146]="*Yāvañcidaṃ bhotā kaccānena guttadvārova samāno guttadvāroti akkhāto.**How accurately you’ve explained someone whose sense doors are guarded!*";
P_HTM[3147]="*Abhikkantaṃ, bho kaccāna; abhikkantaṃ, bho kaccāna.**Excellent, Master Kaccāna! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[3148]="*Seyyathāpi, bho kaccāna, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā kaccānena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Kaccāna has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[3149]="*Esāhaṃ, bho kaccāna, taṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca, bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[3150]="*Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ kaccāno dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ.**From this day forth, may Master Kaccāna remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.*";
P_HTM[3151]="*Yathā ca bhavaṃ kaccāno makkarakate upāsakakulāni upasaṅkamati; evameva lohiccakulaṃ upasaṅkamatu.**Please come to my family just as you go to the families of the lay followers in Makkarakaṭa.*";
P_HTM[3152]="*Tattha ye māṇavakā vā māṇavikā vā bhavantaṃ kaccānaṃ abhivādessanti paccuṭṭhissanti āsanaṃ vā udakaṃ vā dassanti, tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti.**The brahmin boys and girls there will bow to you, rise in your presence, and give you a seat and water. That will be for their lasting welfare and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[3153]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3154]="*10. Verahaccānisuttaṃ**Verahaccāni*";
P_HTM[3155]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā udāyī kāmaṇḍāyaṃ viharati todeyyassa brāhmaṇassa ambavane.**At one time Venerable Udāyī was staying near Kāmaṇḍā in the brahmin Todeyya’s mango grove.*";
P_HTM[3156]="*Atha kho verahaccānigottāya brāhmaṇiyā antevāsī māṇavako yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā udāyinā saddhiṃ sammodi.**Then a boy who was a student of the brahmin lady of the Verahaccāni clan went up to Udāyī and exchanged greetings with him.*";
P_HTM[3157]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[3158]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ māṇavakaṃ āyasmā udāyī dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**Udāyī educated, encouraged, fired up, and inspired that student with a Dhamma talk.*";
P_HTM[3159]="*Atha kho so māṇavako āyasmatā udāyinā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā yena verahaccānigottā brāhmaṇī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā verahaccānigottaṃ brāhmaṇiṃ etadavoca:**Then that student went to the brahmin lady of the Verahaccāni clan and said to her,*";
P_HTM[3160]="*“yagghe, bhoti, jāneyyāsi.**“Please, madam, you should know this.*";
P_HTM[3161]="*Samaṇo udāyī dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ, sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsetī”ti.**The ascetic Udāyī teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure.”*";
P_HTM[3162]="*“Tena hi tvaṃ, māṇavaka, mama vacanena samaṇaṃ udāyiṃ nimantehi svātanāya bhattenā”ti.**“Then, student, invite him in my name for tomorrow’s meal.”*";
P_HTM[3163]="*“Evaṃ, bhotī”ti kho so māṇavako verahaccānigottāya brāhmaṇiyā paṭissutvā yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, madam,” he replied. He went to Udāyī and said,*";
P_HTM[3164]="*“adhivāsetu kira, bhavaṃ udāyī amhākaṃ ācariyabhariyāya verahaccānigottāya brāhmaṇiyā svātanāya bhattan”ti.**“Sir, may Master Udāyī please accept an offering of tomorrow’s meal from my teacher’s wife, the brahmin lady of the Verahaccāni clan.”*";
P_HTM[3165]="*Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā udāyī tuṇhībhāvena.**Udāyī consented in silence.*";
P_HTM[3166]="*Atha kho āyasmā udāyī tassā rattiyā accayena pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena verahaccānigottāya brāhmaṇiyā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Then when the night had passed, Udāyī robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the brahmin lady’s home, and sat down on the seat spread out.*";
P_HTM[3167]="*Atha kho verahaccānigottā brāhmaṇī āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi.**Then the brahmin lady served and satisfied Udāyī with her own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[3168]="*Atha kho verahaccānigottā brāhmaṇī āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ pādukā ārohitvā ucce āsane nisīditvā sīsaṃ oguṇṭhitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:**When Udāyī had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, she put on a pair of shoes, sat on a high seat, covered her head, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3169]="*“bhaṇa, samaṇa, dhamman”ti.**“Ascetic, preach the Dhamma.”*";
P_HTM[3170]="*“Bhavissati, bhagini, samayo”ti vatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkami.**“There will be an occasion for that, sister,” he replied, then got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[3171]="*Dutiyampi kho so māṇavako yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā udāyinā saddhiṃ sammodi.**For a second time that student went to Venerable Udāyī …*";
P_HTM[3172]="*Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.* **";
P_HTM[3173]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ māṇavakaṃ āyasmā udāyī dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.* **";
P_HTM[3174]="*Dutiyampi kho so māṇavako āyasmatā udāyinā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā yena verahaccānigottā brāhmaṇī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā verahaccānigottaṃ brāhmaṇiṃ etadavoca:**And for a second time that student went to the brahmin lady of the Verahaccāni clan …*";
P_HTM[3175]="*“yagghe, bhoti, jāneyyāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3176]="*Samaṇo udāyī dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ, sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāsetī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3177]="*“Evamevaṃ pana tvaṃ, māṇavaka, samaṇassa udāyissa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsasi.**She said to him, “You keep praising the ascetic Udāyī like this.*";
P_HTM[3178]="*Samaṇo panudāyī ‘bhaṇa, samaṇa, dhamman’ti vutto samāno ‘bhavissati, bhagini, samayo’ti vatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkanto”ti.**But when I asked him to preach the Dhamma he just said that there would be an occasion for that, and then he got up and left.”*";
P_HTM[3179]="*“Tathā hi pana tvaṃ, bhoti, pādukā ārohitvā ucce āsane nisīditvā sīsaṃ oguṇṭhitvā etadavoca:**“Madam, that’s because you put on a pair of shoes, sat on a high seat, and covered your head before inviting him to teach.*";
P_HTM[3180]="*‘bhaṇa, samaṇa, dhamman’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3181]="*Dhammagaruno hi te bhavanto dhammagāravā”ti.**For the masters respect the teaching.”*";
P_HTM[3182]="*“Tena hi tvaṃ, māṇavaka, mama vacanena samaṇaṃ udāyiṃ nimantehi svātanāya bhattenā”ti.**“Then, student, invite him in my name for tomorrow’s meal.”*";
P_HTM[3183]="*“Evaṃ, bhotī”ti kho so māṇavako verahaccānigottāya brāhmaṇiyā paṭissutvā yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:**“Yes, madam,” he replied. …*";
P_HTM[3184]="*“adhivāsetu kira bhavaṃ udāyī amhākaṃ ācariyabhariyāya verahaccānigottāya brāhmaṇiyā svātanāya bhattan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3185]="*Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā udāyī tuṇhībhāvena.* **";
P_HTM[3186]="*Atha kho āyasmā udāyī tassā rattiyā accayena pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena verahaccānigottāya brāhmaṇiyā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.* **";
P_HTM[3187]="*Atha kho verahaccānigottā brāhmaṇī āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi.**Then the brahmin lady served and satisfied Udāyī with her own hands with a variety of delicious foods.*";
P_HTM[3188]="*Atha kho verahaccānigottā brāhmaṇī āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ pādukā orohitvā nīce āsane nisīditvā sīsaṃ vivaritvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:**When Udāyī had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, she took off her shoes, sat on a low seat, uncovered her head, and said to him,*";
P_HTM[3189]="*“kismiṃ nu kho, bhante, sati arahanto sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti, kismiṃ asati arahanto sukhadukkhaṃ na paññapentī”ti?**“Sir, when what exists do the perfected ones declare that there is pleasure and pain? When what doesn’t exist do the perfected ones not declare that there is pleasure and pain?”*";
P_HTM[3190]="*“Cakkhusmiṃ kho, bhagini, sati arahanto sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti, cakkhusmiṃ asati arahanto sukhadukkhaṃ na paññapenti … pe …**“Sister, when there’s an eye, the perfected ones declare that there is pleasure and pain. When there’s no eye, the perfected ones don’t declare that there is pleasure and pain.*";
P_HTM[3191]="*jivhāya sati arahanto sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti, jivhāya asati arahanto sukhadukkhaṃ na paññapenti … pe ….**When there’s an ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[3192]="*Manasmiṃ sati arahanto sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti, manasmiṃ asati arahanto sukhadukkhaṃ na paññapentī”ti.**mind, the perfected ones declare that there is pleasure and pain. When there’s no mind, the perfected ones don’t declare that there is pleasure and pain.”*";
P_HTM[3193]="*Evaṃ vutte, verahaccānigottā brāhmaṇī āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca:**When he said this, the brahmin lady said to Udāyī,*";
P_HTM[3194]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante.**“Excellent, sir! Excellent!*";
P_HTM[3195]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ ayyena udāyinā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Venerable Udāyī has made the teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[3196]="*Esāhaṃ, ayya udāyi, taṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca, bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha.*";
P_HTM[3197]="*Upāsikaṃ maṃ ayyo udāyī dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**From this day forth, may Venerable Udāyī remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[3198]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3199]="*Gahapativaggo tatiyo.* **";
P_HTM[3200]="*Vesālī vajji nāḷandā,* **";
P_HTM[3201]="*Bhāradvāja soṇo ca ghosito;* **";
P_HTM[3202]="*Hāliddiko nakulapitā,* **";
P_HTM[3203]="*Lohicco verahaccānīti.* **";
P_HTM[3204]="*14. Devadahavaggo**At Devadaha*";
P_HTM[3205]="*1. Devadahasuttaṃ**At Devadaha*";
P_HTM[3206]="*Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati devadahaṃ nāma sakyānaṃ nigamo.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans, near the Sakyan town named Devadaha.*";
P_HTM[3207]="*Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:**There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:*";
P_HTM[3208]="*“nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sabbesaṃyeva bhikkhūnaṃ chasu phassāyatanesu appamādena karaṇīyanti vadāmi, na ca panāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sabbesaṃyeva bhikkhūnaṃ chasu phassāyatanesu nāppamādena karaṇīyanti vadāmi.**“When it comes to the six fields of contact, mendicants, I don’t say that all mendicants have work to do with diligence, nor do I say that none of them have work to do with diligence.*";
P_HTM[3209]="*Ye te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū arahanto khīṇāsavā vusitavanto katakaraṇīyā ohitabhārā anuppattasadatthā parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojanā sammadaññāvimuttā, tesāhaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ chasu phassāyatanesu nāppamādena karaṇīyanti vadāmi.**I say that, when it comes to the six fields of contact, mendicants don’t have work to do with diligence if they are perfected, with defilements ended, having completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and become rightly freed through enlightenment.*";
P_HTM[3210]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3211]="*Kataṃ tesaṃ appamādena, abhabbā te pamajjituṃ.**They’ve done their work with diligence, and are incapable of negligence.*";
P_HTM[3212]="*Ye ca kho te, bhikkhave, bhikkhū sekkhā appattamānasā anuttaraṃ yogakkhemaṃ patthayamānā viharanti, tesāhaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ chasu phassāyatanesu appamādena karaṇīyanti vadāmi.**I say that, when it comes to the six fields of contact, mendicants do have work to do with diligence if they are trainees, who haven’t achieved their heart’s desire, but live aspiring to the supreme sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[3213]="*Taṃ kissa hetu?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3214]="*Santi, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā manoramāpi, amanoramāpi.**There are sights known by the eye that are pleasant and also those that are unpleasant.*";
P_HTM[3215]="*Tyāssa phussa phussa cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti.**Though experiencing them again and again they don’t occupy the mind.*";
P_HTM[3216]="*Cetaso apariyādānā āraddhaṃ hoti vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ.**Their energy is roused up and unflagging, their mindfulness is established and lucid, their body is tranquil and undisturbed, and their mind is immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3217]="*Imaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appamādaphalaṃ sampassamāno tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ chasu phassāyatanesu appamādena karaṇīyanti vadāmi … pe …**Seeing this fruit of diligence, I say that those mendicants have work to do with diligence when it comes to the six fields of contact. …*";
P_HTM[3218]="*santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā manoramāpi amanoramāpi.**There are thoughts known by the mind that are pleasant and also those that are unpleasant.*";
P_HTM[3219]="*Tyāssa phussa phussa cittaṃ na pariyādāya tiṭṭhanti.**Though experiencing them again and again they don’t occupy the mind.*";
P_HTM[3220]="*Cetaso apariyādānā āraddhaṃ hoti vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ.**Their energy is roused up and unflagging, their mindfulness is established and lucid, their body is tranquil and undisturbed, and their mind is immersed in samādhi.*";
P_HTM[3221]="*Imaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, appamādaphalaṃ sampassamāno tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ chasu phassāyatanesu appamādena karaṇīyanti vadāmī”ti.**Seeing this fruit of diligence, I say that those mendicants have work to do with diligence when it comes to the six fields of contact.”*";
P_HTM[3222]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3223]="*2. Khaṇasuttaṃ**Opportunity*";
P_HTM[3224]="*“Lābhā vo, bhikkhave, suladdhaṃ vo, bhikkhave,**“You’re fortunate, mendicants, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[3225]="*khaṇo vo paṭiladdho brahmacariyavāsāya.**to have the opportunity to live the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[3226]="*Diṭṭhā mayā, bhikkhave, chaphassāyatanikā nāma nirayā.**I’ve seen the hell called ‘the six fields of contact’.*";
P_HTM[3227]="*Tattha yaṃ kiñci cakkhunā rūpaṃ passati aniṭṭharūpaṃyeva passati, no iṭṭharūpaṃ; akantarūpaṃyeva passati, no kantarūpaṃ; amanāparūpaṃyeva passati, no manāparūpaṃ.**There, whatever sight you see with your eye is unlikable, not likable; undesirable, not desirable; unpleasant, not pleasant.*";
P_HTM[3228]="*Yaṃ kiñci sotena saddaṃ suṇāti … pe …**Whatever sound you hear …*";
P_HTM[3229]="*yaṃ kiñci ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyati … pe …**Whatever odor you smell …*";
P_HTM[3230]="*yaṃ kiñci jivhāya rasaṃ sāyati … pe …**Whatever flavor you taste …*";
P_HTM[3231]="*yaṃ kiñci kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusati … pe …**Whatever touch you feel …*";
P_HTM[3232]="*yaṃ kiñci manasā dhammaṃ vijānāti aniṭṭharūpaṃyeva vijānāti, no iṭṭharūpaṃ; akantarūpaṃyeva vijānāti, no kantarūpaṃ; amanāparūpaṃyeva vijānāti, no manāparūpaṃ.**Whatever thought you know with your mind is unlikable, not likable; undesirable, not desirable; unpleasant, not pleasant.*";
P_HTM[3233]="*Lābhā vo, bhikkhave, suladdhaṃ vo, bhikkhave,**You’re fortunate, mendicants, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[3234]="*khaṇo vo paṭiladdho brahmacariyavāsāya.**to have the opportunity to live the spiritual life.*";
P_HTM[3235]="*Diṭṭhā mayā, bhikkhave, chaphassāyatanikā nāma saggā.**I’ve seen the heaven called ‘the six fields of contact’.*";
P_HTM[3236]="*Tattha yaṃ kiñci cakkhunā rūpaṃ passati iṭṭharūpaṃyeva passati, no aniṭṭharūpaṃ; kantarūpaṃyeva passati, no akantarūpaṃ; manāparūpaṃyeva passati, no amanāparūpaṃ … pe …**There, whatever sight you see with your eye is likable, not unlikable; desirable, not undesirable; pleasant, not unpleasant.*";
P_HTM[3237]="*yaṃ kiñci jivhāya rasaṃ sāyati … pe …**Whatever sound … odor … flavor … touch …*";
P_HTM[3238]="*yaṃ kiñci manasā dhammaṃ vijānāti iṭṭharūpaṃyeva vijānāti, no aniṭṭharūpaṃ; kantarūpaṃyeva vijānāti, no akantarūpaṃ; manāparūpaṃyeva vijānāti, no amanāparūpaṃ.**Whatever thought you know with your mind is likable, not unlikable; desirable, not undesirable; pleasant, not unpleasant.*";
P_HTM[3239]="*Lābhā vo, bhikkhave, suladdhaṃ vo, bhikkhave,**You’re fortunate, mendicants, so very fortunate,*";
P_HTM[3240]="*khaṇo vo paṭiladdho brahmacariyavāsāyā”ti.**to have the opportunity to live the spiritual life.”*";
P_HTM[3241]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3242]="*3. Paṭhamarūpārāmasuttaṃ**Liking Sights (1st)*";
P_HTM[3243]="*“Rūpārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā rūparatā rūpasammuditā.**“Mendicants, gods and humans like sights, they love them and enjoy them.*";
P_HTM[3244]="*Rūpavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti.**But when sights perish, fade away, and cease, gods and humans live in suffering.*";
P_HTM[3245]="*Saddārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā saddaratā saddasammuditā.**Gods and humans like sounds …*";
P_HTM[3246]="*Saddavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti.* **";
P_HTM[3247]="*Gandhārāmā …**smells …*";
P_HTM[3248]="*rasārāmā …**tastes …*";
P_HTM[3249]="*phoṭṭhabbārāmā …**touches …*";
P_HTM[3250]="*dhammārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā dhammaratā dhammasammuditā.**thoughts, they love them and enjoy them.*";
P_HTM[3251]="*Dhammavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti.**But when thoughts perish, fade away, and cease, gods and humans live in suffering.*";
P_HTM[3252]="*Tathāgato ca kho, bhikkhave, arahaṃ sammāsambuddho rūpānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā na rūpārāmo na rūparato na rūpasammudito.**The Realized One has truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape of sights, so he doesn’t like, love, or enjoy them.*";
P_HTM[3253]="*Rūpavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā sukho, bhikkhave, tathāgato viharati.**When sights perish, fade away, and cease, the Realized One lives happily.*";
P_HTM[3254]="*Saddānaṃ …**The Realized One has truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape of sounds …*";
P_HTM[3255]="*gandhānaṃ …**smells …*";
P_HTM[3256]="*rasānaṃ …**tastes …*";
P_HTM[3257]="*phoṭṭhabbānaṃ …**touches …*";
P_HTM[3258]="*dhammānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā na dhammārāmo, na dhammarato, na dhammasammudito.**thoughts, so he doesn’t like, love, or enjoy them.*";
P_HTM[3259]="*Dhammavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā sukho, bhikkhave, tathāgato viharati”.**When thoughts perish, fade away, and cease, the Realized One lives happily.”*";
P_HTM[3260]="*Idamavoca bhagavā.**That is what the Buddha said.*";
P_HTM[3261]="*Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:**Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:*";
P_HTM[3262]="*“Rūpā saddā rasā gandhā,**“Sights, sounds, tastes, smells,*";
P_HTM[3263]="*phassā dhammā ca kevalā;**touches and thoughts, the lot of them—*";
P_HTM[3264]="*Iṭṭhā kantā manāpā ca,**they’re likable, desirable, and pleasurable*";
P_HTM[3265]="*yāvatatthīti vuccati.**as long as you can say that they exist.*";
P_HTM[3266]="*Sadevakassa lokassa,**In all the world with its gods,*";
P_HTM[3267]="*ete vo sukhasammatā;**this is reckoned as happiness.*";
P_HTM[3268]="*Yattha cete nirujjhanti,**And where they cease*";
P_HTM[3269]="*taṃ tesaṃ dukkhasammataṃ.**this is reckoned as suffering.*";
P_HTM[3270]="*Sukhaṃ diṭṭhamariyebhi,**The noble ones have seen that happiness*";
P_HTM[3271]="*sakkāyassa nirodhanaṃ;**is the cessation of identity.*";
P_HTM[3272]="*Paccanīkamidaṃ hoti,**Those who see*";
P_HTM[3273]="*sabbalokena passataṃ.**contradict the whole world.*";
P_HTM[3274]="*Yaṃ pare sukhato āhu,**What others say is happiness*";
P_HTM[3275]="*tadariyā āhu dukkhato;**the noble ones say is suffering.*";
P_HTM[3276]="*Yaṃ pare dukkhato āhu,**What others say is suffering*";
P_HTM[3277]="*tadariyā sukhato vidū.**the noble ones say is happiness.*";
P_HTM[3278]="*Passa dhammaṃ durājānaṃ,**See, this teaching is hard to understand,*";
P_HTM[3279]="*sammūḷhettha aviddasu;**it confuses the ignorant.*";
P_HTM[3280]="*Nivutānaṃ tamo hoti,**Those who don’t see are closed off;*";
P_HTM[3281]="*andhakāro apassataṃ.**for them, all is blind darkness.*";
P_HTM[3282]="*Satañca vivaṭaṃ hoti,**But those who see are open;*";
P_HTM[3283]="*āloko passatāmiva;**for the good, it is light.*";
P_HTM[3284]="*Santike na vijānanti,**Though it’s right there, the unskilled fools*";
P_HTM[3285]="*maggā dhammassa akovidā.**don’t understand the teaching.*";
P_HTM[3286]="*Bhavarāgaparetebhi,**They’re mired in desire to be reborn,*";
P_HTM[3287]="*bhavarāgānusārībhi;**flowing along the stream of lives,*";
P_HTM[3288]="*Māradheyyānupannehi,**mired in Māra’s sovereignty:*";
P_HTM[3289]="*nāyaṃ dhammo susambudho.**this teaching isn’t easy for them to understand.*";
P_HTM[3290]="*Ko nu aññatra mariyebhi,**Who, apart from the noble ones,*";
P_HTM[3291]="*Padaṃ sambuddhumarahati;**is qualified to understand this state?*";
P_HTM[3292]="*Yaṃ padaṃ sammadaññāya,**When they’ve rightly understood it,*";
P_HTM[3293]="*Parinibbanti anāsavā”ti.**they’re extinguished without defilements.”*";
P_HTM[3294]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
