P_HTM[3313]="*5. Paṭhamanatumhākaṃsuttaṃ**Not Yours (1st)*";
P_HTM[3314]="*“Yaṃ, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ taṃ pajahatha.**“Mendicants, give up what’s not yours.*";
P_HTM[3315]="*Taṃ vo pahīnaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.**Giving it up will be for your welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3316]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ?**And what isn’t yours?*";
P_HTM[3317]="*Cakkhu, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ; taṃ pajahatha.**The eye isn’t yours: give it up.*";
P_HTM[3318]="*Taṃ vo pahīnaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati … pe …**Giving it up will be for your welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3319]="*jivhā na tumhākaṃ; taṃ pajahatha.**The ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[3320]="*Sā vo pahīnā hitāya sukhāya bhavissati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3321]="*mano na tumhākaṃ; taṃ pajahatha.**mind isn’t yours: give it up.*";
P_HTM[3322]="*So vo pahīno hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.**Giving it up will be for your welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3323]="*Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yaṃ imasmiṃ jetavane tiṇakaṭṭhasākhāpalāsaṃ taṃ jano hareyya vā ḍaheyya vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā kareyya, api nu tumhākaṃ evamassa:**Suppose a person was to carry off the grass, sticks, branches, and leaves in this Jeta’s Grove, or burn them, or do what they want with them. Would you think:*";
P_HTM[3324]="*‘amhe jano harati vā ḍahati vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karotī’”ti?**‘This person is carrying us off, burning us, or doing what they want with us?’”*";
P_HTM[3325]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“No, sir.*";
P_HTM[3326]="*“Taṃ kissa hetu”?**Why is that?*";
P_HTM[3327]="*“Na hi no etaṃ, bhante, attā vā attaniyaṃ vā”ti.**Because that’s neither self nor belonging to self.”*";
P_HTM[3328]="*“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, cakkhu na tumhākaṃ; taṃ pajahatha.**“In the same way, the eye isn’t yours: give it up.*";
P_HTM[3329]="*Taṃ vo pahīnaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati … pe …**Giving it up will be for your welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3330]="*jivhā na tumhākaṃ; taṃ pajahatha.**The ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[3331]="*Sā vo pahīnā hitāya sukhāya bhavissati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3332]="*mano na tumhākaṃ; taṃ pajahatha.**mind isn’t yours: give it up.*";
P_HTM[3333]="*So vo pahīno hitāya sukhāya bhavissatī”ti.**Giving it up will be for your welfare and happiness.”*";
P_HTM[3334]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3335]="*6. Dutiyanatumhākaṃsuttaṃ**Not Yours (2nd)*";
P_HTM[3336]="*“Yaṃ, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ, taṃ pajahatha.**“Mendicants, give up what’s not yours.*";
P_HTM[3337]="*Taṃ vo pahīnaṃ hitāya sukhāya bhavissati.**Giving it up will be for your welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3338]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ?**And what isn’t yours?*";
P_HTM[3339]="*Rūpā, bhikkhave, na tumhākaṃ;**Sights aren’t yours: give them up.*";
P_HTM[3340]="*te pajahatha. Te vo pahīnā hitāya sukhāya bhavissanti.**Giving them up will be for your welfare and happiness.*";
P_HTM[3341]="*Saddā …**Sounds …*";
P_HTM[3342]="*gandhā …**smells …*";
