P_HTM[3351]="*7. Ajjhattāniccahetusuttaṃ**Interior and Cause Are Impermanent*";
P_HTM[3352]="*“Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ.**“Mendicants, the eye is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3353]="*Yopi hetu, yopi paccayo cakkhussa uppādāya, sopi anicco.**The cause and condition that gives rise to the eye is also impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3354]="*Aniccasambhūtaṃ, bhikkhave, cakkhu kuto niccaṃ bhavissati … pe …**Since the eye is produced by what is impermanent, how could it be permanent?*";
P_HTM[3355]="*jivhā aniccā.**The ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[3356]="*Yopi hetu, yopi paccayo jivhāya uppādāya sopi anicco.* **";
P_HTM[3357]="*Aniccasambhūtā, bhikkhave, jivhā kuto niccā bhavissati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3358]="*mano anicco.**mind is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3359]="*Yopi, bhikkhave, hetu yopi paccayo manassa uppādāya, sopi anicco.**The cause and condition that gives rise to the mind is also impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3360]="*Aniccasambhūto, bhikkhave, mano kuto nicco bhavissati.**Since the mind is produced by what is impermanent, how could it be permanent?*";
P_HTM[3361]="*Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati … pe … jivhāyapi nibbindati … pe … manasmimpi nibbindati,**Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind.*";
P_HTM[3362]="*nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti.**Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed.*";
P_HTM[3363]="*‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[3364]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3365]="*8. Ajjhattadukkhahetusuttaṃ**Interior and Cause Are Suffering*";
P_HTM[3366]="*“Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, dukkhaṃ.**“Mendicants, the eye is suffering.*";
P_HTM[3367]="*Yopi hetu yopi paccayo cakkhussa uppādāya, sopi dukkho.**The cause and condition that gives rise to the eye is also suffering.*";
P_HTM[3368]="*Dukkhasambhūtaṃ, bhikkhave, cakkhu kuto sukhaṃ bhavissati … pe …**Since the eye is produced by what is suffering, how could it be happiness?*";
P_HTM[3369]="*jivhā dukkhā.**The ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[3370]="*Yopi hetu, yopi paccayo jivhāya uppādāya, sopi dukkho.* **";
P_HTM[3371]="*Dukkhasambhūtā, bhikkhave, jivhā kuto sukhā bhavissati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3372]="*mano dukkho.**mind is suffering.*";
P_HTM[3373]="*Yopi hetu yopi paccayo manassa uppādāya, sopi dukkho.**The cause and condition that gives rise to the mind is also suffering.*";
P_HTM[3374]="*Dukkhasambhūto, bhikkhave, mano kuto sukho bhavissati.**Since the mind is produced by what is suffering, how could it be happiness?*";
P_HTM[3375]="*Evaṃ passaṃ … pe …**Seeing this …*";
P_HTM[3376]="*nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[3377]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3378]="*9. Ajjhattānattahetusuttaṃ**Interior and Cause Are Not*";
P_HTM[3379]="*“Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, anattā.**“Mendicants, the eye is not-self.*";
P_HTM[3380]="*Yopi hetu, yopi paccayo cakkhussa uppādāya, sopi anattā.**The cause and condition that gives rise to the eye is also not-self.*";
P_HTM[3381]="*Anattasambhūtaṃ, bhikkhave, cakkhu kuto attā bhavissati … pe …**Since the eye is produced by what is not-self, how could it be self?*";
P_HTM[3382]="*jivhā anattā.**The ear … nose … tongue … body …*";
P_HTM[3383]="*Yopi hetu yopi paccayo jivhāya uppādāya, sopi anattā.* **";
P_HTM[3384]="*Anattasambhūtā, bhikkhave, jivhā kuto attā bhavissati … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3385]="*mano anattā.**mind is not-self.*";
P_HTM[3386]="*Yopi hetu yopi paccayo manassa uppādāya, sopi anattā.**The cause and condition that gives rise to the mind is also not-self.*";
P_HTM[3387]="*Anattasambhūto, bhikkhave, mano kuto attā bhavissati.**Since the mind is produced by what is not-self, how could it be self?*";
P_HTM[3388]="*Evaṃ passaṃ … pe …**Seeing this …*";
P_HTM[3389]="*nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[3390]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3391]="*10. Bāhirāniccahetusuttaṃ**Exterior and Cause Are Impermanent*";
P_HTM[3392]="*“Rūpā, bhikkhave, aniccā.**“Mendicants, sights are impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3393]="*Yopi hetu, yopi paccayo rūpānaṃ uppādāya, sopi anicco.**The cause and condition that gives rise to sights is also impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3394]="*Aniccasambhūtā, bhikkhave, rūpā kuto niccā bhavissanti.**Since sights are produced by what is impermanent, how could they be permanent?*";
P_HTM[3395]="*Saddā …**Sounds …*";
P_HTM[3396]="*gandhā …**Smells …*";
P_HTM[3397]="*rasā …**Tastes …*";
P_HTM[3398]="*phoṭṭhabbā …**Touches …*";
P_HTM[3399]="*dhammā aniccā.**Thoughts are impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3400]="*Yopi hetu, yopi paccayo dhammānaṃ uppādāya, sopi anicco.**The cause and condition that gives rise to thoughts is also impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3401]="*Aniccasambhūtā, bhikkhave, dhammā kuto niccā bhavissanti.**Since thoughts are produced by what is impermanent, how could they be permanent?*";
P_HTM[3402]="*Evaṃ passaṃ … pe …**Seeing this …*";
P_HTM[3403]="*nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[3404]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3405]="*11. Bāhiradukkhahetusuttaṃ**Exterior and Cause Are Suffering*";
P_HTM[3406]="*“Rūpā, bhikkhave, dukkhā.**“Mendicants, sights are suffering.*";
P_HTM[3407]="*Yopi hetu, yopi paccayo rūpānaṃ uppādāya, sopi dukkho.**The cause and condition that gives rise to sights is also suffering.*";
P_HTM[3408]="*Dukkhasambhūtā, bhikkhave, rūpā kuto sukhā bhavissanti.**Since sights are produced by what is suffering, how could they be happiness?*";
P_HTM[3409]="*Saddā …**Sounds …*";
P_HTM[3410]="*gandhā …**Smells …*";
P_HTM[3411]="*rasā …**Tastes …*";
P_HTM[3412]="*phoṭṭhabbā …**Touches …*";
P_HTM[3413]="*dhammā dukkhā.**Thoughts are suffering.*";
P_HTM[3414]="*Yopi hetu, yopi paccayo dhammānaṃ uppādāya, sopi dukkho.**The cause and condition that gives rise to thoughts is also suffering.*";
P_HTM[3415]="*Dukkhasambhūtā, bhikkhave, dhammā kuto sukhā bhavissanti.**Since thoughts are produced by what is suffering, how could they be happiness?*";
P_HTM[3416]="*Evaṃ passaṃ … pe …**Seeing this …*";
P_HTM[3417]="*nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti.**They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’”*";
P_HTM[3418]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3419]="*12. Bāhirānattahetusuttaṃ**Exterior and Cause Are Not*";
P_HTM[3420]="*“Rūpā, bhikkhave, anattā.**“Mendicants, sights are not-self.*";
