P_HTM[3849]="*17. Saṭṭhipeyyālavaggo**Sixty Abbreviated Texts*";
P_HTM[3850]="*1. Ajjhattaaniccachandasuttaṃ**Desire for the Impermanent Interior*";
P_HTM[3851]="*“Yaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ, tatra vo chando pahātabbo.**“Mendicants, you should give up desire for what is impermanent.*";
P_HTM[3852]="*Kiñca, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ?**And what is impermanent?*";
P_HTM[3853]="*Cakkhu, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ; tatra vo chando pahātabbo … pe …**The eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind are impermanent:*";
P_HTM[3854]="*jivhā aniccā; tatra vo chando pahātabbo … pe …* **";
P_HTM[3855]="*mano anicco; tatra vo chando pahātabbo.**you should give up desire for them.*";
P_HTM[3856]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ, tatra vo chando pahātabbo”ti.**You should give up desire for what is impermanent.”*";
P_HTM[3857]="*2. Ajjhattaaniccarāgasuttaṃ**Greed for the Impermanent Interior*";
