P_HTM[6632]="*Atha kho sakko devānamindo pañcahi devatāsatehi saddhiṃ yenāyasmā mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:**Then Sakka, lord of gods, with five hundred deities came up to Mahāmoggallāna, bowed, and stood to one side. Mahāmoggallāna said to him:*";
P_HTM[6633]="*“Sādhu kho, devānaminda, buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgamanaṃ hoti:**“Lord of gods, it’s good to have experiential confidence in the Buddha:*";
P_HTM[6634]="*‘itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti.**‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha … teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’*";
