P_HTM[8078]="*Gāmaṇisaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ.**The Linked Discourses on chiefs are complete.*";
P_HTM[8079]="*43. Asaṅkhatasaṃyuttaṃ* **";
P_HTM[8080]="*1. Aniccavaggo**The First Chapter*";
P_HTM[8081]="*1. Kāyagatāsatisuttaṃ**Mindfulness of the Body*";
P_HTM[8082]="*Sāvatthinidānaṃ.**At Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[8083]="*“Asaṅkhatañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi asaṅkhatagāmiñca maggaṃ.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the unconditioned and the path that leads to the unconditioned.*";
P_HTM[8084]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[8085]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhataṃ?**And what is the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8086]="*Yo, bhikkhave, rāgakkhayo dosakkhayo mohakkhayo—**The ending of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[8087]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhataṃ.**This is called the unconditioned.*";
P_HTM[8088]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8089]="*Kāyagatāsati.**Mindfulness of the body.*";
P_HTM[8090]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo.**This is called the path that leads to the unconditioned.*";
P_HTM[8091]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, desitaṃ vo mayā asaṅkhataṃ, desito asaṅkhatagāmimaggo.**So, mendicants, I’ve taught you the unconditioned and the path that leads to the unconditioned.*";
P_HTM[8092]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ upādāya, kataṃ vo taṃ mayā.**Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best for their disciples.*";
P_HTM[8093]="*Etāni, bhikkhave, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni. Jhāyatha, bhikkhave, mā pamādattha; mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha. Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti.**Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice absorption, mendicants! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is my instruction to you.”*";
P_HTM[8094]="*Paṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8095]="*2. Samathavipassanāsuttaṃ**Serenity and Discernment*";
P_HTM[8096]="*“Asaṅkhatañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi asaṅkhatagāmiñca maggaṃ.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the unconditioned and the path that leads to the unconditioned.*";
P_HTM[8097]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[8098]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhataṃ?**And what is the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8099]="*Yo, bhikkhave, rāgakkhayo dosakkhayo mohakkhayo—**The ending of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[8100]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhataṃ.**This is called the unconditioned.*";
P_HTM[8101]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8102]="*Samatho ca vipassanā ca.**Serenity and discernment.*";
P_HTM[8103]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo … pe ….**This is called the path that leads to the unconditioned. …”*";
P_HTM[8104]="*Dutiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8105]="*3. Savitakkasavicārasuttaṃ**Placing the Mind and Keeping it Connected*";
P_HTM[8106]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**“And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8107]="*Savitakkasavicāro samādhi, avitakkavicāramatto samādhi, avitakkaavicāro samādhi—ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo … pe ….**Immersion with placing the mind and keeping it connected. Immersion without placing the mind, but just keeping it connected. Immersion without placing the mind or keeping it connected. …”*";
P_HTM[8108]="*Tatiyaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8109]="*4. Suññatasamādhisuttaṃ**Emptiness Immersion*";
P_HTM[8110]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**“And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8111]="*Suññato samādhi, animitto samādhi, appaṇihito samādhi—ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo … pe ….**Emptiness immersion; signless immersion; undirected immersion. …”*";
P_HTM[8112]="*Catutthaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8113]="*5. Satipaṭṭhānasuttaṃ**Mindfulness Meditation*";
P_HTM[8114]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**“And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8115]="*Cattāro satipaṭṭhānā. Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo … pe ….**The four kinds of mindfulness meditation. …”*";
P_HTM[8116]="*Pañcamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8117]="*6. Sammappadhānasuttaṃ**Right Efforts*";
P_HTM[8118]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**“And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8119]="*Cattāro sammappadhānā. Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo … pe ….**The four right efforts. …”*";
P_HTM[8120]="*Chaṭṭhaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8121]="*7. Iddhipādasuttaṃ**Bases of Psychic Power*";
P_HTM[8122]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**“And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8123]="*Cattāro iddhipādā. Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo … pe ….**The four bases of psychic power. …”*";
P_HTM[8124]="*Sattamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8125]="*8. Indriyasuttaṃ**Faculties*";
P_HTM[8126]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**“And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8127]="*Pañcindriyāni. Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo … pe ….**The five faculties. …”*";
P_HTM[8128]="*Aṭṭhamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8129]="*9. Balasuttaṃ**Powers*";
P_HTM[8130]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**“And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8131]="*Pañca balāni. Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo … pe ….**The five powers. …”*";
P_HTM[8132]="*Navamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8133]="*10. Bojjhaṅgasuttaṃ**Awakening Factors*";
P_HTM[8134]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**“And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8135]="*Satta bojjhaṅgā. Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo … pe ….**The seven awakening factors. …”*";
P_HTM[8136]="*Dasamaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[8137]="*11. Maggaṅgasuttaṃ**The Path*";
P_HTM[8138]="*“Katamo ca, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo?**“And what is the path that leads to the unconditioned?*";
P_HTM[8139]="*Ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo.**The noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[8140]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, asaṅkhatagāmimaggo.**This is called the path that leads to the unconditioned.*";
P_HTM[8141]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, desitaṃ vo mayā asaṅkhataṃ, desito asaṅkhatagāmimaggo.**So, mendicants, I’ve taught you the unconditioned and the path that leads to the unconditioned.*";
P_HTM[8142]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ upādāya kataṃ vo taṃ mayā.**Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best for their disciples.*";
P_HTM[8143]="*Etāni, bhikkhave, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni. Jhāyatha, bhikkhave, mā pamādattha; mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha. Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti.**Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice absorption, mendicants! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is my instruction to you.”*";
P_HTM[8144]="*Ekādasamaṃ.* **";
