P_HTM[8353]="*33. Parāyanasuttaṃ**The Haven*";
P_HTM[8354]="*“Parāyanañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi parāyanagāmiñca maggaṃ.**“Mendicants, I will teach you the haven and the path that leads to the haven.*";
P_HTM[8355]="*Taṃ suṇātha.**Listen …*";
P_HTM[8356]="*Katamañca, bhikkhave, parāyanaṃ?**And what is the haven?*";
P_HTM[8357]="*Yo, bhikkhave, rāgakkhayo dosakkhayo mohakkhayo—**The ending of greed, hate, and delusion.*";
P_HTM[8358]="*idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, parāyanaṃ.**This is called the haven.*";
P_HTM[8359]="*Katamo ca, bhikkhave, parāyanagāmī maggo?**And what is the path that leads to the haven?*";
P_HTM[8360]="*Kāyagatāsati.**Mindfulness of the body.*";
P_HTM[8361]="*Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, parāyanagāmimaggo.**This is called the path that leads to the haven.*";
P_HTM[8362]="*Iti kho, bhikkhave, desitaṃ vo mayā parāyanaṃ, desito parāyanagāmimaggo.**So, mendicants, I’ve taught you the haven and the path that leads to the haven.*";
P_HTM[8363]="*Yaṃ, bhikkhave, satthārā karaṇīyaṃ sāvakānaṃ hitesinā anukampakena anukampaṃ upādāya, kataṃ vo taṃ mayā.**Out of compassion, I’ve done what a teacher should do who wants what’s best for their disciples.*";
P_HTM[8364]="*Etāni, bhikkhave, rukkhamūlāni, etāni suññāgārāni. Jhāyatha, bhikkhave, mā pamādattha; mā pacchā vippaṭisārino ahuvattha. Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī”ti.**Here are these roots of trees, and here are these empty huts. Practice absorption, mendicants! Don’t be negligent! Don’t regret it later! This is my instruction to you.”*";
P_HTM[8365]="*(Yathā asaṅkhataṃ tathā vitthāretabbaṃ.) (33)**(This should be expanded as with the unconditioned.)*";
P_HTM[8366]="*Tettiṃsatimaṃ.* **";
